description: As Jonathan Pearce wrestles Joanderson Brito against the fence, Brito shoots his arm through and locks up ninja choke, following Pearce down to the canvas as he earns the tap.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig

name: GEORGES ST-PIERRE | UFC 65
description: UFC Hall of Famer Georges "Rush" St-Pierre lands a perfectly timed head kick followed by heavy ground and pound on Matt Hughes to become the new welterweight champion.
event: UFC 65

name: RAFAEL FIZIEV | UFC 256
description: UFC lightweight Rafael "Ataman" Fiziev rips a left hand to the body of Renato Carneiro to start a picture-perfect combination that ends with a devastating left hook, earning Fiziev the knockout win.
event: UFC 256

name: SEAN O'MALLEY | UFC 250
description: A subtle feint from bantamweight star "Sugar" Sean O'Malley allows for an uncontested straight right to knock out Eddie Wineland at UFC 250.
event: UFC 250

name: ALEX MORONO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 13, 2023
description: Halfway into the second round, Tim Means ducks under a spinning back fist, straight into the arm-in guillotine of Alex "The Great White" Morono. Morono sits up to reposition his arms and wraps Means into full guard, finishing the choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Almeida

name: ANDREA LEE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 19, 2018
description: In her UFC debut, Andrea "KGB" Lee showcases her excellent grappling in a victory over Veronica Macedo.

name: ANDRE PETROSKI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 28, 2021
description: In his UFC debut, Andre Petroski wrestles Micheal Gillmore to the canvas and drops heavy elbows to secure the TKO victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Barboza vs Chikadze

name: MIESHA TATE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 25, 2015
description: Miesha "Cupcake" Tate knocks Jessica Eye down with a big overhand right early on in their fight en route to a unanimous decision victory where she won every round on the three judge's scorecards.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dillashaw vs Barao 2

name: ALEX PEREIRA | UFC 276
description: In his biggest fight to date Alex "Poatan" Pereira seizes the opportunity, leaning into a powerful left hook that sends Sean Strickland to the canvas, and a right hand follow-up forces the referee to step in and call a stop to the contest.
event: UFC 276

name: TJ DILLASHAW | UFC 158
description: Before his time as bantamweight champion of the world, TJ Dillashaw earned a stellar finish against Issei Tamura, feinting a right hand before landing his patented right high kick, ending the fight in round two.
event: UFC 158

name: DEIVESON FIGUEIREDO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 18, 2020
description: Deiveson "Deus Da Guerra" Figueiredo submits Joseph Benavidez via a rear-naked choke after dominating the first round, winning the vacant flyweight title.
event: UFC Fight Night: Figueiredo vs Benavidez 2

name: RASHAD EVANS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 25, 2007
description: UFC Hall of Famer "Suga" Rashad Evans lands one of the most eye-popping head kick knockouts you'll ever see early in the second round of his fight with Sean Salmon.
event: UFC Fight Night: Evans vs Salmon

name: PADDY PIMBLETT | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEP 4, 2021
description: Paddy "The Baddy" Pimblett earns a TKO victory landing a series of punches against Luigi Vendramini, in his UFC debut.
event: UFC Fight Night: Brunson vs Till

name: JULIO ARCE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 18, 2019
description: Julio Arce knocks out Julian Erosa with an impressive kick to the head in the 3rd round of a hard fought contest.
event: UFC Fight Night: dos Anjos vs Lee

name: PEDRO MUNHOZ | UFC 235
description: Pedro "The Young Punisher" Munhoz weathers the storm from Cody Garbrandt as the two exchange wild haymakers one after the other, before Munhoz lands a shot that drops Garbrandt and ends the fight.
event: UFC 235

name: CODY GARBRANDT | UFC 202
description: Cody "No Love" Garbrandt needs less than a minute to send Takeya Mizugaki flying to the floor with a perfect combination, and a barrage of strikes immediately follows to give Garbrandt the TKO win.
event: UFC 202

name: DANIEL CORMIER | UFC 173
description: UFC Hall of Famer Daniel "DC" Cormier outclasses Dan Henderson for three rounds, ultimately locking in a rear-naked choke late in the final round and earning a technical submission victory at UFC 173.
event: UFC 173

name: TJ DILLASHAW | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 11, 2012
description: Former bantamweight champion, TJ Dillashaw finishes Vaughan Lee via rear naked choke from standing body triangle on his way up the 135lb ranks. This is one of the first fights that Dillashaw mixed his tactical, stance switching kickboxing style with his NCAA wrestling pedigree.
event: UFC Fight Night: Munoz vs Weidman

name: LEON EDWARDS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 11, 2015
description: Leon "Rocky" Edwards ends the fight with a knockout only eight seconds into the bout to record one of the fastest finishes in UFC history, securing his first win with the promotion.
event: UFC Fight Night: Gonzaga vs Cro Cop 2

name: TOM ASPINALL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEP 4, 2021
description: UFC heavyweight Tom Aspinall lands a knee to the body and immediately stuns Serghei Spivac with a lightning-quick right elbow that spelled the beginning of the end for Spivac.
event: UFC Fight Night: Brunson vs Till

name: MOLLY MCCANN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 19, 2022
description: In spectacular fashion, "Meatball" Molly McCann becomes the first woman in UFC history to finish an opponent via spinning back elbow.
event: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Aspinall

name: VALENTINA SHEVCHENKO | UFC 238
description: Valentina "Bullet" Shevchenko wows the Chicago crowd at UFC 238, knocking out Jessica Eye with a stunning head kick to defend her flyweight title.
event: UFC 238

name: RAFAEL DOS ANJOS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 23, 2014
description: In the first of many UFC main event appearances, Rafael Dos Anjos upset former lightweight champion Benson Henderson via TKO in round one. Swinging hard and fast early in the first round, Dos Anjos lands an unusual flying double knee to rock Henderson and follows up with a massive left hook to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Henderson vs dos Anjos

name: THE LAST STYLEBENDER
description: Israel "The Last Stylebender" Adesanya brought the heat at UFC 243 in 2019, starting with this flashy choreographed walkout routine that brought the Australian crowd to its feet before he made his way to the Octagon to unify the middleweight title.

name: LEON EDWARDS | UFC 278
description: Leon "Rocky" Edwards shocks defending champion Kamaru Usman and the Salt Lake City crowd at UFC 278 with a head kick knockout in the final minute of the fifth round to claim the undisputed title for himself.
event: UFC 278

name: MACKENZIE DERN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 30, 2020
description: Mackenzie Dern takes the fight to the ground where she is most dangerous and pulls off an impressive kneebar submission against Hannah Cifers.
event: UFC Fight Night: Woodley vs Burns

name: KHAMZAT CHIMAEV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 16, 2020
description: Khamzat "Borz" Chimaev makes quite the impression in his UFC debut by dominating John Phillips from beginning to end of their fight, earning a submission victory in the second round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Kattar vs Ige

name: ROYCE GRACIE | UFC 4
description: Pioneer and UFC Hall of Famer Royce Gracie uses his patented Jiu-Jitsu to submit Dan Severn in the final round of the historical UFC 4 tournament via triangle choke. The win marks Gracie's third UFC tournament victory.
event: UFC 4

name: FRANK MIR | UFC 140
description: Frank Mir clashes with fellow submission artist Minotauro Nogueira at UFC 140 and earns the technical submission victory via Kimura in the opening round.
event: UFC 140

name: DUSTIN POIRIER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 14, 2018
description: Dustin "The Diamond" Poirier wins a slugfest main event bout versus Justin Gaethje via TKO after an eruption of strikes in the fourth round from Poirier proves to be too much.
event: UFC Fight Night: Poirier vs Gaethje

name: MICHAEL BISPING | UFC 199
description: On just 17 days notice, UFC Hall of Famer Michael "The Count" Bisping knocks out Luke Rockhold in the first round of their rematch fight at UFC 199 to claim the middleweight title and becomes the first British champion in UFC history.
event: UFC 199

name: SONG YADONG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 12, 2022
description: A powerful combination ending with an uppercut earns bantamweight Song Yadong the walk-off knockout victory over Marlon Moraes in the co-main event of a UFC Fight Night event in Las Vegas.
event: UFC Fight Night: Santos vs Ankalaev

name: STIPE MIOCIC | UFC 198

event: UFC 198

name: JOSH EMMETT | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 30, 2019
description: Josh Emmett connects on a big overhand right after feinting a level change for a one-punch knockout of Michael Johnson at a UFC Fight Night event in Philadelphia.
event: UFC Fight Night: Barboza vs Gaethje

name: QUINTON JACKSON | UFC 92

event: UFC 92

name: DAN HENDERSON | UFC 100
description: Dan "Hendo" Henderson produces one of the most electrifying knockouts you'll ever see at the historic UFC 100 event in his bout with Michael Bisping.
event: UFC 100

name: JOE PYFER | UFC 287
description: Finishing one of the most prolific middleweight submission artists in the UFC on his way up the ranks, Joe "Bodybagz" Pyfer pushed Gerald Meerschaert against the fence and landed a massive left hook to floor the veteran before following up with ground and pound to finish.
event: UFC 287

name: IM NOT SURPRISED
description: After defeating Conor McGregor and shocking the world at UFC 196, Nate Diaz summed up the performance with one iconic phrase.

name: CHEICK KONGO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 26, 2011
description: Incredibly, Cheick Kongo leaves the Octagon victorious after his main event bout versus Pat Barry ends in unbelievable fashion that you have to see to believe.
event: UFC Fight Night: Kongo vs Barry

name: AMANDA NUNES | UFC 232
description: In just the fourth instance in UFC history where champions from different divisions fought for the same title, women's bantamweight champion Amanda "The Lioness" Nunes challenged fellow featherweight champion Cris Cyborg for the women's featherweight title at UFC 232. In a stunning display of speed and power, Nunes shocked the world by knocking Cyborg out 51 seconds into the first round, joining the prestigious ranks of two-division champions and staking her claim as the greatest women's fighter of all time.
event: UFC 232

name: MAGOMED MUSTAFAEV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 20, 2019
description: A spinning back kick from Magomed "The Sniper" Mustafaev knocks Rafael Fiziev to the canvas where Mustafaev swarms the lightweight and earns the TKO victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Overeem vs Oleinik

name: ANDREI ARLOVSKI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEPT 13, 2014
description: The first right hand from Andrei "The Pitbull" Arlovski stuns Antonio "Bigfoot" Silva, and the second right hook sends the Brazilian heavyweight to the canvas in the main event of their UFC Fight Night bout in Brasilia.
event: UFC Fight Night: Bigfoot vs Arlovski

name: ALEX PEREIRA | UFC 268
description: In his first-ever UFC appearance, Alex "Poatan" Pereira showed what all the hype was about with this vicious jumping knee KO against Andreas Michailidis. Early in the second round, Pereira jumps into a switch knee that lands flush to the face of Michailidis, finishing the fight via KO.
event: UFC 268

name: JUSTIN GAETHJE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 30, 2019
description: Justin "The Highlight" Gaethje catches Edson Barboza with his hands down against the fence and lands a knockout punch in the first round of their main event clash in Philadelphia.
event: UFC Fight Night: Barboza vs Gaethje

name: MIRANDA MAVERICK | UFC 291
description: Rebounding from a close decision loss to Jasmine Jasudavicius, Miranda "Fear The" Maverick got back to her dominant grappling ways against Priscila Cachoeira. Maverick works her way to mount late in round three, and as Cachoeira extends her arm to frame, Maverick swings her left leg over the head of Cachoeira, sitting back to finish the armbar.
event: UFC 291

name: SHAVKAT RAKHMONOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 25, 2022
description: Shavkat "Nomad" Rakhmonov continues his rise up the welterweight division by dominating Neil Magny, submitting him in the second round via a guillotine choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Tsarukyan vs Gamrot

name: BROCK LESNAR | UFC 87
description: Brock Lesnar wastes no time forcing the action at UFC 87 by landing a huge right hand that drops Heath Herring shortly after the opening bell. Lesnar would go on to earn his first UFC win via unanimous decision victory.
event: UFC 87

name: SHAVKAT RAKHMONOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 05, 2022
description: After submission victories in his first two UFC fights, Shavkat "Nomad" Rakhmonov looked to showcase his striking against Carlston "Mocambique" Harris at UFC Fight Night: Hermansson vs Strickland. With a minute left in the first round, Rakhmonov unleashed a perfectly timed spinning hook kick that sent Harris to the canvas, followed by ground-and-pound to secure the knockout victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Hermansson vs Strickland

name: ANDERSON SILVA | PRIDE FC 2003
description: Anderson "The Spider" Silva crosses paths with former UFC welterweight champion Carlos "The Ronin" Newton while competing for PRIDE FC in 2003 and lands a spectacular flying knee KO.
event: PRIDE FC 2003

name: JON JONES | UFC 128
description: Jon "Bones" Jones puts together a dominating performance at UFC 128 against Shogun Rua to become the youngest fighter ever to claim UFC gold.
event: UFC 128

name: BELAL MUHAMMAD | UFC 242
description: Belal "Remember The Name" Muhammad controls the action against Takashi Sato at UFC 242 earning the submission victory via rear-naked choke in the third round.
event: UFC 242

name: ALEXANDER VOLKOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 17, 2018
description: UFC heavyweight Alexander "Drago" Volkov scores the biggest win of his career so far, via a fourth-round knockout of former champion Fabricio Werdum in London.
event: UFC Fight Night: Werdum vs Volkov

name: ZABIT MAGOMEDSHARIPOV | UFC 228
description: Zabit Magomedsharipov pulls off a seldomly-seen submission via banana split in his matchup with Brandon Davis at UFC 228.
event: UFC 228

name: CARLOS PRATES | UFC 305
description: Riding a two-fight win streak to begin his UFC career, Dana White's Contender Series alum Carlos "The Nightmare" Prates stepped into the Octagon against veteran Li Jingliang at UFC 305. At the tail end of the second round, Prates uncorked a devastating left hook that handed Jingliang the first knockout loss of his 17-year career, earning Performance of the Night honors.
event: UFC 305

name: ILIA TOPURIA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 19, 2022
description: Ilia "El Matador" Topuria stands in the pocket and delivers a ferocious combination of strikes to knock out Jai Herbert in the second round of their bout in London.
event: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Aspinall

name: JAMAHAL HILL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 19, 2022
description: A right hand in the first round from Jamahal "Sweet Dreams" Hill leads to one of the most dramatic knockouts of the year against Johnny Walker in their main event matchup.
event: UFC Fight Night: Walker vs Hill

name: GLOVER TEIXEIRA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 27, 2019
description: Glover Teixeira doesn't let the opportunity go by when Ion Cutelaba shows his back in the second round and secures the submission via rear-naked choke for the 10th finish of his UFC career.
event: UFC Fight Night: Jacare vs Hermansson

name: BRANDON MORENO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 1, 2016

event: UFC Fight Night: Lineker vs Dodson

name: BRIAN ORTEGA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 9, 2017
description: In his first-ever UFC main event and en route to his first shot at UFC gold, Brian "T-City" Ortega submitted UFC Veteran Cub Swanson, who himself was just two fights removed from his Hall of Fame win over Dooho Choi. Crowding Swanson's boxing with his clinch work, Ortega throws a knee against the fence and wraps up Swanson's exposed neck, jumping full guard and making minor adjustments to finish his world-class guillotine.
event: UFC Fight Night: Swanson vs Ortega

name: FRANKIE EDGAR | UFC 136
description: A right hand from Frankie "The Answer" Edgar rocks Gray Maynard in their trilogy fight at UFC 136 before a barrage of strikes against the fence knocks Maynard to the ground. Edgar then puts a stamp on his lightweight title defense with some strong ground-and-pound that ends the fight.
event: UFC 136

name: MOHAMMED USMAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 6, 2022
description: Mohammed "The Motor" Usman puts a stamp on his winning run during The Ultimate Fighter: Team Pena vs Team Nunes. The brother of former UFC champion Kamaru Usman, "The Motor" possesses an athleticism rarely seen at heavyweight, and his power makes him a problem for anyone in the division.
event: UFC Fight Night: Santos vs Hill

name: MIRKO CRO COP | PRIDE FC 2006
description: Mirko "Cro Cop" Filipovic knocks out Wanderlei Silva with a head kick during their 2006 rematch, resulting in one of the most memorable finishes in PRIDE FC history.
event: PRIDE FC 2006

name: JAIR ROZENSTRUIK | UFC 282
description: Jair Rozenstruik lands a beautiful jab that rocks Chris Daukaus and follows up with a barrage of punches and a flying knee, ultimately finishing the heavyweight bout with a stunning knockout victory at UFC 282, solidifying his reputation as one of the most feared strikers in the division.
event: UFC 282

name: ILIA TOPURIA | UFC 282
description: After stuffing a majority of Bryce Mitchell's takedown attempts for the first two rounds, Ilia "El Matador" Topuria wrestles Mitchell against the fence, locking up a head and arm triangle and using it to throw his opponent to the floor, earning the tap moments later near the end of the third round.
event: UFC 282

description: Long before his reign as UFC flyweight champion, Brandon "The Assassin Baby" Moreno made a promise after his Performance of the Night bonus submission at UFC Fight Night: Swanson vs Lobov, saying "I will become Champion one day." Moreno would go on to live up to this prediction.

name: MICHAL OLEKSIEJCZUK | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 26, 2023
description: Poland's Michal Oleksiejczuk ended the fight early against Chidi Njokuani, dropping him several times on the feet until he was able to land some ground and pound to find a finish in round 1.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs The Korean Zombie

name: CORY SANDHAGEN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 6, 2021
description: Cory Sandhagen calls for the bantamweight title after his highlight knockout of UFC legend Frankie Edgar via flying knee only 28 seconds into the 1st-round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Overeem vs Volkov

name: KEVIN RANDLEMAN | PRIDE FC 2004
description: UFC Hall of Famer Kevin "The Monster" Randleman rocks Mirko Cro Cop with a left hook and finishes their 2004 PRIDE FC fight with some ground and pound for a shocking upset.
event: PRIDE FC 2004

name: UMAR NURMAGOMEDOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 14, 2023
description: Seemingly out of nowhere, Umar Nurmagomedov scores a stunning knockout finish against Raoni Barcelos in the first round of their bantamweight contest.
event: UFC Fight Night: Strickland vs Imavov

name: ISLAM MAKHACHEV | UFC 259
description: Islam Makhachev shows off his elite grappling and wrestling prowess for two rounds before eventually submitting Drew Dober in the third via arm-triangle choke at UFC 259.
event: UFC 259

name: IAN GARRY | UFC 285
description: Ian "The Future" Garry stuns UFC fans with his explosive knockout victory over Song Kenan, displaying the elite striking skills that make him a highly touted prospect from Ireland.
event: UFC 285

name: BROCK LESNAR | UFC 116
description: After weathering the storm early, Brock Lesnar turns the tide taking Shane Carwin down and transitioning to an arm-triangle for the submission to defend and unify his heavyweight title at UFC 116.
event: UFC 116

description: After stringing together a four-fight win streak against a who's who of the heavyweight division, Fabricio "Vai Cavalo" Werdum faced Mark Hunt for the interim title at UFC 180. Midway through the second round, Werdum unleashed a flying knee, dropping Hunt to the canvas and finishing the fight with a flurry of ground strikes to earn the title at the promotion's first-ever event in Mexico.
event: UFC 180

name: YANAL ASHMOUZ | UFC 286
description: Yanal "Red Fox" Ashmouz uses a creative combination to overwhelm Sam Patterson in the first round at UFC 286 and earn the knockout victory in just 75 seconds.
event: UFC 286

name: DANIEL CORMIER | UFC 230
description: Defending his heavyweight title at UFC 230, Daniel "DC" Cormier took on the hard-hitting Derrick "The Black Beast" Lewis. Cormier's superior wrestling dominated the first round as he easily took Lewis down and controlled the action on the ground. Early in the second, Cormier secured another takedown, transitioned to back control, and locked in a rear-naked choke, earning the submission victory and making history as the first fighter to successfully defend titles in two weight classes in UFC history.
event: UFC 230

name: MINOTAURO NOGUEIRA | PRIDE FC 2003
description: Minotauro Nogueira claims the PRIDE FC interim heavyweight title with a thrilling armbar submission against Mirko Cro Cop in their 2003 matchup.
event: PRIDE FC 2003

name: TAILA SANTOS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 20, 2021
description: Taila Santos takes the back and sinks in the rear-naked choke vs Joanne Wood earning herself a top-ranked spot in the division and ultimately a shot at the women's flyweight title.
event: UFC Fight Night: Vieira vs Tate

name: DON FRYE | PRIDE FC 2002
description: Don "The Predator" Frye narrowly defeats Ken Shamrock after the two exchange body shots during the February 2002 classic grudge match in the PRIDE FC ring.
event: PRIDE FC 2002

name: SEAN STRICKLAND | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 14, 2020
description: Sean Strickland pieces up Brendan Allen on the feet with some nice combinations and earns himself a Performance of the Night bonus after his TKO win in the second round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Felder vs dos Anjos

name: JACK DELLA MADDALENA | UFC 284
description: Jack Della Maddalena drops Randy Brown with a beautiful hook before hitting a slick submission at UFC 284, proving that he's a force to be reckoned within the welterweight division.
event: UFC 284

name: JAILTON MALHADINHO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 5, 2022
description: Dana White's Contender Series alum Jailton "Malhadinho" Almeida showcases his strength and athleticism in his UFC debut, securing a first-round TKO win over Danilo Marques.
event: UFC Fight Night: Hermansson vs Strickland

name: BO NICKAL | UFC 285
description: With two 1st-round submission victories on DWCS, Bo Nickal lives up to the hype in his UFC debut by submitting UFC veteran Jamie Pickett via arm-triangle choke in the 1st-round.
event: UFC 285

name: ISRAEL ADESANYA | UFC 230
description: Israel "The Last Stylebender" Adesanya puts on a striking clinic, overwhelming Derek Brunson with a flurry of punches after a perfectly-timed knee, securing a TKO victory in the first round and solidifying his status as a top middleweight contender
event: UFC 230

name: BRIAN ORTEGA | UFC 222
description: Taking advantage of his first PPV co-main spot at UFC 222, Brian "T-City" Ortega lands some big shots and knocks out Frankie Edgar with a sensational uppercut in the first round.
event: UFC 222

name: IKRAM ALISKEROV | UFC 288
description: Dana White's Contender Series alumni Ikram Aliskerov makes the most of his UFC debut, putting UFC veteran Phil Hawes out at UFC 288 with a right cross after a frantic exchange on the feet in the first round.
event: UFC 288

name: KENNEDY NZECHUKWU | UFC 259
description: Kennedy "African Savage" Nzechukwu drops talented striker Carlos Ulberg with a commanding right hook in an electric Fight of The Night.
event: UFC 259

name: MICHAEL BISPING | UFC 127
description: Seeking revenge for one of the most bizarre diss tracks ever released by a fighter, Michael "The Count" Bisping puts a pace on Jorge Rivera and pummels him against the fence, finding a TKO stoppage in round 2.
event: UFC 127
