description: After becoming the fourth simultaneous two-division champion in UFC history in 2019, Henry "Triple C" Cejudo overwhelms Dominick Cruz in the second round of their bout at UFC 249 to earn the TKO win and successfully defend his bantamweight title.
event: UFC 249

name: WANDERLEI SILVA | PRIDE FC 2003
description: Wanderlei "The Brazilian Axe Murderer" Silva makes it a perfect three victories against Kazushi Sakuraba with a knockout punch in the opening round of the PRIDE FC 2003 Middleweight Grand Prix.
event: PRIDE FC 2003

name: JAILTON ALMEIDA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 13, 2023
description: With physical attributes that make him a nightmare matchup for anyone at heavyweight or light heavyweight, Jailton "Malhadinho" Almeida is one of the most skilled grapplers in the world, dominating fellow contenders like Jair Rozenstruik with little resistance. Almeida methodically works into increasingly dominant positions, eventually throwing significant ground and pound strikes in mount, forcing Rozenstruik to turn to his back and expose the neck for a rear naked choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Almeida

name: FRANKIE EDGAR | THE ULTIMATE FIGHTER SEASON 22 FINALE
description: Former lightweight champion, Frankie "The Answer" Edgar earns his second shot at 145lb legend, Jose Aldo with this massive knockout of Chad Mendes.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 22 Finale

name: YAIR RODRIGUEZ | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 18, 2019
description: Yair "El Pantera" Rodriguez shows off his creative striking ability in his rematch with Jeremy Stephens, landing a crippling kick to the body and sweeping Stephen's leg to send him to the canvas.
event: UFC Fight Night: Reyes vs Weidman

name: DAN IGE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 13, 2021
description: Dan "50K" Ige stuns Gavin Tucker with a perfectly timed right hand, securing the victory a mere :22 seconds into the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Edwards vs Muhammad

name: SERGEI PAVLOVICH | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 3, 2022
description: Sergei Pavlovich made quick work of Tai Tuivasa in their highly anticipated heavyweight clash, stunning the Australian with a series of powerful hooks that sent him crashing to the canvas and leading to the TKO victory for Pavlovich in the first round. With this impressive win, Pavlovich solidifies himself as a top contender in the UFC's heavyweight division.
event: UFC Fight Night: Thompson vs Holland

name: AMANDA NUNES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 8, 2015
description: Amanda "The Lioness" Nunes defends several takedown attempts from Olympic silver medalist Sara McMann and eventually finds the rear-naked choke finish in round one after punishing her on the feet.
event: UFC Fight Night: Teixeira vs Saint Preux

name: ROBBIE LAWLER | UFC 173
description: After facing adversity early in the third round, Lawler feints with his lead right hand, setting up a perfect knee that drops Ellenberger, finishing the fight via TKO. His follow-up fight-of-the-night bonus victory over Matt Brown would earn him a rematch with Johny Hendricks for the welterweight title.
event: UFC 173

name: KHABIB TIME
description: UFC Hall of Famer Khabib "The Eagle" Nurmagomedov forgot what time it was at a 2018 press conference and had to ask President Dana White if he could please tell the crowd in attendance.

name: HENRY CEJUDO | UFC 215
description: Henry "Triple C" Cejudo defeats Wilson Reis via a second-round KO, showcasing his lightning fast striking skills and solidifying his position as a top bantamweight in UFC. This fight was the beginning of Cejudo's run to the title and his future status as a Champion.
event: UFC 215

name: BRUNO SILVA | UFC 269
description: Bruno "Blindado" Silva lands a staggering two-punch combination on Jordan Wright before finishing with some dominant ground-and-pound to win via TKO.
event: UFC 269

name: KELVIN GASTELUM | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 25, 2017
description: Kelvin Gastelum slips a punch and connects with his own right hook, overhand left combo finishing UFC Hall-of-Famer Michael Bisping via 1st-round knockout in the main event of the evening.
event: UFC Fight Night: Bisping vs Gastelum

name: JENS PULVER | UFC 28
description: Jens "Little Evil" Pulver ends the night early, knocking out 6'0 lightweight veteran John Lewis with a big left hook just 15 seconds into round one. Pulver would later go on to defeat BJ Penn for the lightweight title.
event: UFC 28

name: URIJAH FABER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 13, 2013
description: "The California Kid" Urijah Faber finishes his long-time friend and training partner Scott Jorgensen via rear naked choke in round one in The Ultimate Fighter Finale: Team Jones vs Team Sonnen main event. Faber stepped in to face Jorgensen on short notice after Demetrious Johnson withdrew from the headlining bout.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 17 Finale

name: ALJAMAIN STERLING | UFC 228
description: Aljamain "Funk Master" Sterling delivers heavy ground-and-pound from the back mount vs Cody Stamann before securing the submission becoming the 2nd-ever UFC athlete to win by Suloev stretch.
event: UFC 228

name: LERONE MURPHY | UFC 267
description: Lerone "The Miracle" Murphy lands a perfectly-timed knee against wrestling specialist Makwan Amirkhani to earn his 2nd-career knockout finish and remain undefeated in UFC.
event: UFC 267

name: JAN BLACHOWICZ | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 15, 2020
description: En route to his title victory at UFC 253, Jan Blachowicz put his legendary Polish power on full display in his rematch against Corey Anderson. After trading on the feet for most of the first round, Anderson advances forward into a perfectly timed straight hand from Blachowicz, ending the fight via KO.
event: UFC Fight Night: Anderson vs Blachowicz

name: GEOFF NEAL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 06, 2022
description: Geoff "Handz of Steel" Neal lands a jab, straight right-hand combination flush to the temple of Vicente Luque, sending him to the fence in a daze, and follows up with a flurry of successive uppercuts, finding the straight left knockout blow shortly after.
event: UFC Fight Night: Santos vs Hill

name: KHALIL ROUNTREE JR. | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEP 4, 2021
description: Utilizing a variation of the oblique kick to great effect, Khalil Rountree Jr. silenced the UFC Apex with a devastating side kick landed on the knee of Modestas Bukauskas.
event: UFC Fight Night: Brunson vs Till

name: ANTHONY HERNANDEZ | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 20, 2023
description: Anthony "Fluffy" Hernandez proved that he is one of the most dangerous middleweight prospects in the world against Edmen Shahbazyan, dominating the final two rounds with his grappling and pace before finding a TKO stoppage.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dern vs Hill

name: CALVIN KATTAR | UFC 249
description: Calvin Kattar made waves with this signature victory over Jeremy Stephens. Mid-way through the second round, Kattar fakes a jab to close distance and lands a thunderous right elbow to the jaw of Jeremy Stephens, knocking out the UFC veteran.
event: UFC 249

name: CONOR MCGREGOR | UFC 178
description: Kicking off a rivalry that would go on to define the legacy of Dustin Poirier, "The Notorious" Conor McGregor made quick work of "The Diamond" at featherweight, landing a left-hand flush to the temple and finishing with several follow-up shots in round 1.
event: UFC 178

name: YOU SUCK 2.0
description: Putting a stamp on the highest profile knockout of his career, Matt "The Steamrolla" Frevola pays homage to "The Bad Guy" Chael Sonnen, recreating his iconic callout of Anderson Silva saying, "Paddy Pimblett, you absolutely suck!".

name: MATT SERRA | UFC 109
description: Following a short, feeling-out process in the first half of round 1, former welterweight champion Matt Serra drops Frank Trigg with a two-hook combination after working his way into range with punches, earning an early KO victory.
event: UFC 109

name: MYKTYBEK OROLBAI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 18, 2023
description: Turning heads in his UFC debut, Kyrgyzstan's Myktybek Orolbai dominated Uros Medic for as long as the fight lasted, using his grappling to maintain control until he found the neck crank submission in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig

name: PAUL CRAIG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 19, 2022
description: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Aspinall featured great performances from UK fighters across the board and this submission victory from Paul "BearJew" Craig was no exception. After getting taken down and controlled for a majority of the first round, Craig locks up a triangle as Nikita Krylov lands a punch from top position and uses his hands to tighten the choke, finishing his fourth triangle choke submission in his UFC career.
event: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Aspinall

name: CUB SWANSON | UFC 152
description: Following his stoppage victories over Ross Pearson and George Roop, UFC Veteran Cub Swanson lands a nasty left hook to the body of a young Charles Oliveira, then connects with a massive overhand right. The blow stuns Oliveira for a moment until he eventually drops to the canvas, bringing an end to the contest in round 1.
event: UFC 152

name: MATT FREVOLA | UFC 270
description: Matt "TheSteamRolla" Frevola earns the tremendous TKO victory with some heavy ground and pound after flattening out Genaro Valdez Soto in back mount.
event: UFC 270

name: JI YEON KIM | UFC 243
description: Ji Yeon "Fire Fist" Kim connects with two powerful right hands to the body of Nadia Kassem to secure a last-second knockout victory.
event: UFC 243

name: ROMAN KOPYLOV | UFC 291
description: Russian kickboxing prospect Roman Kopylov has some serious knockout power that he put on full display in his bout with Claudio Ribeiro at UFC 291. Just Moments into the second round, Kopylov feints a low kick and brings it up top to the temple of Ribeiro, winning via head kick KO.
event: UFC 291

name: JULIO ARCE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 24, 2021
description: Making his debut at bantamweight, Julio Arce put the division on notice with this impressive standing TKO victory over Andre Ewell. Late in the second round, Arce connects with a straight left hand, putting Ewell on skates with his back on the fence. Sensing the finish, Arce pressed forward, landing heavy strikes in the blitz, until the referee had seen enough.
event: UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Dillashaw

name: CHARLES JOHNSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 14, 2023
description: Jiu-Jitsu ace Jimmy Flick attempts to implement his tricky attacks from guard, but Charles Johnson doesn't allow it, reigning down blows from top position until achieving the TKO stoppage.
event: UFC Fight Night: Strickland vs Imavov

name: JOSE ALDO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 28, 2018
description: Jose Aldo rebounds from his second loss to Max Holloway in style with this signature win over Jeremy Stephens. After getting rocked early in the first round, Aldo feints an overhand right then digs a perfectly-placed left hook to the liver, finishing Stephens via TKO.
event: UFC Fight Night: Alvarez vs Poirier 2

name: ALEKSANDAR RAKIC | UFC 231
description: One of the most talented light heavyweight prospects on the UFC roster, Aleksandar "Rocket" Rakic outclassed Devin Clark on the feet, utilizing his leg kicks to draw Clark in and then landing an awkward backhand punch to knock Clark out.
event: UFC 231

name: MATEUSZ GAMROT | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 17, 2021
description: Making short work of UFC veteran Jeremy Stephens, Mateusz Gamrot wrestles his way to top half guard early in the first round and as Stephens locks on to a kimura from the bottom, Gamrot steps over the head of Stephens and isolates the arm, finishing a kimura of his own soon after.
event: UFC Fight Night: Makhachev vs Moises

name: JOANNA JEDRZEJCZYK | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 20, 2015
description: In her first strawweight title defense, Joanna Jedrzejczyk outstruck Jessica Penne from bell to bell, putting on a Muay Thai clinic and eventually earning a TKO stoppage. Stuffing nearly every takedown over the course of the fight, Joanna peppers Penne with shots to the legs, head, and body, delivering a big knee through the guard of a wilting Penne, stopping the fight late in round 3.
event: UFC Fight Night: Jedrzejczyk vs Penne

name: SEAN BRADY | UFC 259
description: After dominating the grappling exchanges for the first two rounds, Sean Brady smothers Jake Matthews against the fence, constantly attacking the neck until he secures an arm-triangle choke in round 3.
event: UFC 259

name: HAKEEM DAWODU | UFC 240
description: Mean Hakeem Dawodu lived up to his namesake at UFC 240: Holloway vs Edgar, punishing Yoshinori Horie over three rounds with nasty strikes before landing a head kick KO in front of his home crowd.
event: UFC 240

name: RICKY SIMON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APRIL 21, 2018
description: One of the most well-aged victories in the bantamweight division, Ricky Simon finished Merab "The Machine" Dvalishvili via technical submission in the final seconds of round 3. Simon has Dvalishvili in a deep guillotine choke by the end of the round, and while it appears that the clock runs out before the fight is called, the referee rules that it is a submission stoppage since Dvalishvili is unconscious.
event: UFC Fight Night: Barboza vs Lee

name: PETR YAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 23, 2018
description: In his promotional debut, former bantamweight champion Petr "No Mercy" Yan knocked out UFC veteran Teruto Ishihara in the first round, showcasing the disciplined, punishing muay thai that would become a trademark of his career. Using his striking to pressure Ishihara against the fence, Yan throws a big overhand left in the pocket, connecting with the chin of Ishihara to find the finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Cowboy vs Edwards

name: MICHAEL MORALES | UFC 270
description: One of Ecuador's most dangerous prospects, Michael Morales, showed that he could come back from early adversity in a fight and win against welterweight mainstay Trevin Giles. After getting dropped early in the first round, Morales recomposes himself and finds the chin of Giles, following up with an overhand right that ends the fight.
event: UFC 270

name: MAGOMED ANKALAEV | UFC 254
description: When the first fight ended with a controversial stoppage, Magomed Ankalaev left no doubt in his rematch with Ion Cutelaba, knocking him out with a two-punch combination late in the first round.
event: UFC 254

name: DRAKKAR KLOSE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 2, 2023
description: One of the most consistent lightweights on the planet, Drakkar Klose landed the first of two back-to-back slam knockouts at UFC Fight Night: Dariush vs Tsarukyan. As Joe Solecki attempted to attack an armbar from his back halfway through round 1, Klose picked Solecki up and slammed him down, ending the fight emphatically.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dariush vs Tsarukyan

name: CARLA ESPARZA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 22, 2021
description: Carla "The Cookie Monster" Esparza handed strawweight Chinese powerhouse Yan Xiaonan her first UFC defeat en route to her second title opportunity. Dominating with her wrestling for most of the fight, Ezsparza put Xiaonan in the crucifix position halfway into the second round, raining down elbows and punches until earning the TKO stoppage.
event: UFC Fight Night: Font vs Garbrandt

name: ZHANG WEILI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 24, 2018
description: Before her reign as UFC Champion, "Magnum" Zhang Weili was finishing the best in the world seemingly at will. In her second UFC fight, Weili locks Jessica Aguilar in a triangle choke, using elbows to soften Aguilar up until she exposes her arm, leading to the submission finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Blaydes vs Ngannou 2

name: YAN XIAONAN | UFC 288
description: Strawweight contender Yan Xiaonan knocked out Jessica Andrade in dramatic fashion at UFC 288, stepping back and sitting down on a straight right-hand flush to the jaw of an oncoming Andrade.
event: UFC 288

name: GRANT DAWSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 5, 2022
description: On his way up the lightweight ranks, Grant "KGD" Dawson faced a challenging stylistic matchup with Olympic medalist Mark Madsen and passed with flying colors. Utilizing his leg kicks to immobilize Madsen, Grant Dawson forces his way to Madsen's back, locking up a rear naked choke late in the third round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rodriguez vs Lemos

name: MACY CHIASSON | THE ULTIMATE FIGHTER SEASON 28 FINALE
description: Macy Chiasson submitted Pannie Kianzad to become the The Ultimate Fighter: Heavy Hitters featherweight winner. After defending an armbar in the second round, Chiasson wrestles up to the back of Kianzad, securing a rear naked choke with a gable grip.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 28 Finale

name: JON JONES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 1, 2010
description: Before establishing his legacy as the best light heavyweight of all time, Jon "Bones" Jones dominated Vladimir Matyushenko from the crucifix position, raining down elbows until the TKO stoppage in round 1.
event: UFC Fight Night: Jones vs Matyushenko

name: MERAB DVALISHVILI | UFC 266
description: Known for his seemingly endless cardio output, Merab "The Machine" Dvalishvili put a pace on knockout artist Marlon Moraes at UFC 266, which put the entire division on notice. After getting hurt early in the fight, Dvalishvili recomposed himself and proceeded to overwhelm Moraes with ground and pound until the TKO stoppage in round 3.
event: UFC 266

name: MUHAMMAD MOKAEV | UFC 280
description: One of the most talented flyweight prospects in the world, Muhammad Mokaev, proved that he could dig deep late in a fight against Malcolm Gordon at UFC 280. In the final minute of the third round, Mokaev jumps to the back of Gordon, slips off over the top, but catches the arm on the way down, fully extending to finish the armbar.
event: UFC 280

name: ERIN BLANCHFIELD | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 4, 2022
description: Showcasing a grappling pedigree unlike any other contender at flyweight, Erin "Cold Blooded" Blanchfield proved she is a force to be reckoned with in her fight against JJ Aldrich. After knocking down Aldrich in the second round, Blanchfield jumps to the front headlock position, pushing Aldrich to the fence and adjusting her hands until she finishes a high-elbow guillotine.
event: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Rozenstruik

name: MATTHEW SEMELSBERGER | UFC 266
description: Former collegiate football player Matthew "Semi The Jedi" Semelsberger wasted no time in his welterweight clash with Martin Sano at UFC 266, landing a massive overhand right just 15 seconds into the first round that folded Sano immediately.
event: UFC 266

name: MAYCEE BARBER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 24, 2023
description: In one of the most exciting rounds of 2023, Maycee "The Future" Baber stopped Amanda Ribas via TKO in round 2 in front of a roaring Jacksonville crowd. Barber lands a big head kick followed by an overhand right to stun Ribas, then throws a massive 1, 2 combination to sit her down, finishing with several hammer fists.
event: UFC Fight Night: Emmett vs Topuria

name: RINAT FAKHRETDINOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 1, 2023
description: Returning to the UFC after a two-year hiatus, former title challenger Kevin Lee was swiftly rebuffed by Rinat "Gladiator" Fakhretdinov, who landed a massive right punch early in the first round and sunk in a guillotine choke shortly after to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Strickland vs Magomedov

name: CHARLES OLIVEIRA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 28, 2023
description: Landing one of the rarest submissions ever seen in MMA, Charles "do Bronx" Oliveira showed off his world-class jiu-jitsu early in his UFC career against Eric Wisely. While passing guard, Oliveira sits back into a traditional ashi garami position, and as Wisely rolls to escape, Oliveira transitions into a calf slicer, pulling his way up to Wisely's back and finishing the submission.
event: UFC Fight Night: Evans vs Davis

name: AMANDA LEMOS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 17, 2021
description: Possessing power rarely seen at strawweight, Amanda Lemos put the division on notice with her knockout victory over Montserrat Conejo. Just moments into the first round, Lemos steps back and counters Canejo hard as she steps in to land a jab and then follows up with a combination to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Makhachev vs Moises

name: TABATHA RICCI | UFC 285
description: One of the most exciting prospects in the strawweight division Tabatha "Baby Shark" Ricci showed her world-class grappling against UFC veteran Jessica Penne at UFC 285. After trading strikes to start the fight, Ricci hits Penne with a beautiful throw in the clinch, controlling top position until she steps over to find a far-side armbar.
event: UFC 285

name: BRENDAN ALLEN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 18, 2019
description: Wrestling his way to top position halfway through the second round, Brendan "All-In" Allen wears on Kevin Holland and works his way to the back, finishing the fight via rear naked choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Reyes vs Weidman

name: ROY NELSON | THE ULTIMATE FIGHTER SEASON 16 FINALE
description: In The Ultimate Fighter Finale: Team Carwin vs Team Nelson, Matt Mitrione steps in on short notice to replace and faceoff against his former teammate, the heavy-handed fan favorite Roy "Big Country" Nelson. After finding his range, Nelson steps in with a right uppercut that stuns Mitrione and follows up with a left hook, overhand right combination that finishes the fight in the first round.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 16 Finale

name: GEORGES ST-PIERRE | UFC 217
description: Four years removed from his title defense at UFC 167, the greatest Canadian fighter of all time, Georges "Rush" St-Pierre, returned to the Octagon to realize the crowning achievement of his career: becoming a two-division UFC champion. After landing a massive left hook that dropped Bisping late in the third round, St-Pierre transitioned to the back, securing a rear-naked choke that earned him the middleweight title.
event: UFC 217

name: BRYAN BATTLE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 13, 2023
description: Bryan "Pooh Bear" Battle connects with a thunderous right hook, knocking out Gabe Green in under 20 seconds in front of his hometown in Charlotte, NC. After winning the middleweight tournament during season 29 of The Ultimate Fighter, Battle moved south to the welterweight division, winning two of his first three 170-pound bouts via first-round knockout.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Almeida

name: TATIANA SUAREZ | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 25, 2023
description: After more than three years away from the Octagon, Tatiana Suarez puts the flyweight division back on notice with a dominating performance and submission win over Montana De La Rosa to stay undefeated.
event: UFC Fight Night: Muniz vs Allen

name: MANUEL TORRES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 17, 2023
description: One of the most exciting lightweight prospects in the world, Mexican-born Manuel "El Loco" Torres is a finisher of the highest order, winning 13 of his 14 wins via KO/TKO(7) or submission(6). True to form, Torres defeated Nikolas Motta in the first round at UFC Fight Night: Vettori vs Cannonier, using a crow hop to land a thunderous left elbow.
event: UFC Fight Night: Vettori vs Cannonier

name: BRYCE MITCHELL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 7, 2019
description: After controlling Matt Sayles for the entirety of the first round, Bryce "Thug Nasty" Mitchell locks down the left leg of his opponent while controlling the far-side wrist. Mitchell then systematically peels the right arm of Sayles over his head and wraps up the neck, finishing one of the most devastating and rare submissions in MMA: the twister.
event: UFC Fight Night: Overeem vs Rozenstruik

name: STIPE MIOCIC | UFC 211
description: In his second UFC heavyweight title defense, Stipe Miocic makes quick work of former champion Junior Dos Santos in their rematch at UFC 211 via a first-round TKO victory.
event: UFC 211

name: ALEXANDER VOLKANOVSKI | UFC 232
description: Before his legendary reign as featherweight king, Alexander "The Great" Volkanovski showed that in a division full of sharks, he was a cut above the rest in his masterful performance against Chad Mendes. Overwhelming Mendes with his footwork and feints, Volkanovski backs Mendes against the fence and finishes the fight with massive combinations in round 2.
event: UFC 232

name: DUSTIN POIRIER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 28, 2018
description: Dustin "The Diamond" Poirier connects with a flurry of strikes that sends former champion Eddie Alvarez to the fence, following up with two massive knees in the clinch, and finishing the fight with a short left elbow in the second round. This win primed Dustin Poirier for another rematch against an all-time great Max Holloway, this time for the interim lightweight title.
event: UFC Fight Night: Alvarez vs Poirier 2

name: ARMAN TSARUKYAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 26, 2022
description: One of Islam Makhachev's toughest challenges to date, Arman "Ahalkalakets" Tsarukyan outmatched fellow lightweight standout Joel Alvarez with suffocating top pressure, reigning down big punches from the leg ride position and utilizing the "Dagestani handcuff" to control Alvarez until the eventual TKO finish in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Makhachev vs Green

name: JARED CANNONIER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUN 17, 2023
description: The Killa Gorilla Jared Cannonier put on a striking clinic against Marvin Vettori, keeping his composure and countering hard over the course of five rounds.
event: UFC Fight Night: Vettori vs Cannonier

name: CAMERON SAAIMAN | UFC 290
description: Defending the early takedown attempts of Terrence Mitchell, South African bantamweight prospect Cameron Saaiman settles into the rhythm of the fight, deliberately moving from position to position, eventually flattening Mitchell out and finishing the fight via TKO with ground and pound from back mount.
event: UFC 290

name: CIRYL GANE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEPT 3, 2022
description: Headlining the first UFC event ever held in France, Ciryl "Bon Gamin" Gane gives his hometown fans something to cheer about with a third-round KO against Tai Tuivasa.
event: UFC Fight Night: Gane vs Tuivasa

name: VIRNA JANDIROBA | UFC 252
description: Brazilian jiu-jitsu specialist Virna Jandiroba shoots a takedown immediately in round one and never lets up on Felice Herrig, working her way to mount and snatching up an armbar.
event: UFC 252

name: TYSON PEDRO | UFC 293
description: Kicking off the UFC 293 Main Card, Australian-born light heavyweight Tyson Pedro lands a 1,2 combination mid-way through the first round, rocking Anton Turkalj. Pedro then follows up with a flurry of combinations until he lands a massive straight right that finishes the fight.
event: UFC 293

name: GILBERT BURNS | UFC 283
description: World-class jiu-jitsu player Gilbert "Durinho" Burns finished one of the most experienced welterweights on the UFC roster, Neil Magny, at UFC 283: Teixeira vs Hill. Burns systematically worked his way from a takedown against the fence to half guard, then transitioned to side control and later to mount, eventually pushing Magny's arm across to lock in the head and arm choke.
event: UFC 283

name: ALEXA GRASSO | UFC 285
description: In a shocking upset over long-reigning champion Valentina Shevchenko, Alex Grasso capitalized on an ill-thrown spinning backkick by Shevchenko, closing the distance and taking her back. Grasso then systematically controlled Shevchenko on the ground, digging her arm under the chin to find a rear naked choke finish.
event: UFC 285

name: MATEUSZ REBECKI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 24, 2023
description: After chewing apart Loik Radzhabov's legs with kicks in the first round, Mateusz Rebecki throws a big overhand left to floor Radzhabov, capping off a dominant striking performance.
event: UFC Fight Night: Emmett vs Topuria

name: MIESHA TATE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 17, 2021
description: After a five-year break from competition, Miesha "Cupcake" Tate reminded the world why she is one of the all-time best female fighters ever to do it. Pushing a pace for the entirety of the fight, Tate wears on Marion Reneau with punches and elbows from top position until Reneau eventually turns her back, ending the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Makhachev vs Moises

name: MACKENZIE DERN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 10, 2021
description: Punching her way into the clinch, world-class Jiu-Jitsu practitioner Mackenzie Dern systematically controls Nina Nunes from position to position, taking advantage of mistakes left behind at every step, finding the armbar submission late in round one.
event: UFC Fight Night: Vettori vs Holland

name: ISLAM MAKHACHEV | UFC 267
description: Islam Makhachev fights for the kimura finish against Dan Hooker, and breaks into the lightweight Top 5.
event: UFC 267

name: REMEMBER MY NAME
description: After knocking out Jessica Andrade for the UFC Strawweight title, Zhang Weili proclaimed "My name is Zhang Weili. I am from China. Remember me!" to a roaring home crowd, becoming the first Chinese champion in UFC history.

name: MARTIN BUDAY | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 12, 2023
description: After using an underhook to reverse position and take Josh Parisian down against the fence, Martin Buday maintains control of the arm and attacks a kimura, continually making adjustments to get the tap and earn the submission victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Luque vs Dos Anjos

name: NAZIM SADYKHOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUL 15, 2023
description: After negating several submission attempts from Terrance McKinney during the first round, Nazim Sadykhov stuffs a shot early in round 2, forcing his way to McKinney's back while trapping the left arm. With no hand available to defend his neck, McKinney is forced to tap to the rear naked choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holm vs Bueno Silva

name: SEAN STRICKLAND | UFC 293
description: As much a Cinderella story as the UFC has ever seen, middleweight veteran Sean Strickland not only beat all-time great champion Israel Adesanya in decisive fashion, he did so in Adesanya's area of specialty, kickboxing, shocking the entire world.
event: UFC 293

name: MIKE MALOTT | UFC 289
description: In front of his home crowd in Vancouver, "Proper" Mike Malott continues his 100% finish rate in UFC with this massive submission victory over Adam Fugitt. Late in the second round, Malott feints with a marching front right knee up the middle and carries through with a right hook, left straight combination to drop Fugitt. He then latches onto a Guillotine choke to earn the tap.
event: UFC 289

name: JULIANNA PENA | THE ULTIMATE FIGHTER SEASON 18 FINALE
description: Putting a stamp on the Ronda Rousey and Miesha Tate rivalry of during season 18 of The Ultimate Figher, Julianna "The Venezuelan Vixen" Pena finishes Jessica Rakoczy via TKO in the final seconds of round one, earning a UFC contract in the process.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 18 Finale

name: ALEKSEI OLEINIK | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 15, 2017
description: Landing his patented ezekiel choke for the first time in his UFC career, Octagon veteran Aleksei Oleinik allows Viktor Pesta to transition to mount while sneakily setting up this devestarting and rare choke from bottom.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rodriguez vs Penn

name: CHRISTIAN DUNCAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 18, 2023
description: UK knockout artist Christian "CLD" Duncan proved that he could find a finish at any range against Denis Tiuliulin, landing massive uppercuts inside the clinch and finishing with elbows in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig

name: JALIN TURNER | UFC 276
description: Breaking into the top 15 in short fashion, Jalin "The Tarantula" Turner cracked Brad Riddell early in the first round at UFC 276, jumping on a mounted guillotine immediately and sinching up the choke in less than a minute.
event: UFC 276

name: DA'MON BLACKSHEAR | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 03, 2023
description: While Luan Lacerda inverts to attack a leg, Da'Mon Blackshear keeps his hips heavy, landing heavy ground and pound until the TKO finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Kara-France vs Albazi

name: IASMIN LUCINDO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 12, 2023
description: The youngest female fighter in UFC, Iasmin Lucindo earns her first Octagon finish over fellow fan favorite, Polyana Viana after tripping her to the mat, transitioning to full mount, and forcing her way to a head and arm choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Luque vs Dos Anjos

name: DAVID ONAMA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 19, 2022
description: Showcasing the lighting-fast striking that would become of a staple of his UFC career, David Onama knocks Gabriel Benitez out with a flurry of punches against the fence near the end of round 1.
event: UFC Fight Night: Walker vs Hill

name: JUSTIN GAETHJE | UFC 249
description: Justin "The Highlight" Gaethje showcases elite striking in a TKO victory against Tony Ferguson to claim the interim lightweight title.
event: UFC 249

name: NICHOLAS MAXIMOV | UFC 266
description: Nicholas Maximov earns the unanimous decision victory over Cody Brundage after taking the back and deploying constant ground and pound.
event: UFC 266

name: IRENE ALDANA | UFC 245
description: With just 15 seconds left in a hotly contested first round, Irene Aldana leaps into a left hook that lands flush to the chin of Ketlen Vieira, showing the one-shot knockout power that earned her a shot at the bantamweight title.
event: UFC 245

name: VICENTE LUQUE | UFC 260
description: After landing several thunderous combinations that force former welterweight champion Tyron Woodley to shoot in desperation, "The Silent Assassin" Vicente Luque jumps on a D'arce, sliding his hips through, trapping Woodley against the fence, and tying up the legs to finish the choke.
event: UFC 260

name: CORY SANDHAGEN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 10, 2020
description: In a tactical match between two of the best strikers to ever compete at bantamweight, Cory Sandhagen knocked out Marlon Moraes in impressive fashion, landing a spinning heel kick to the head of Moraes early in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Moraes vs Sandhagen

name: LEON EDWARDS | UFC 286
description: Eliminating any doubt following one of the most sensational come-back knockout victories in UFC history, Leon "Rocky" Edwards proved that he was the best welterweight in the world for a second time at UFC 286, outclassing Kamaru Usman from horn to horn.
event: UFC 286

name: TATIANA SUAREZ | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 5, 2023
description: A standout grappling talent unlike any other in the strawweight division, Tatiana Suarez burst into the top 5 with this dominant performance over former champion, Jessica Andrade. Early in the second round, Suarez forced her way to the front headlock position and pulled guard to lock in the guillotine finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Font

name: CHARLES OLIVEIRA | UFC 289
description: Rebounding from his loss to lightweight champion Islam Makhachev, Charles "Do Bronx" Oliveira stopped the 8-fight win streak of perennial contender Beniel Dariush at UFC 289, using his pressure-heavy striking to secure the TKO finish.
event: UFC 289

name: ROBERT WHITTAKER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 15, 2017
description: Seeking to extend his six-fight win streak and earn a shot at the UFC middleweight title, Robert "The Reaper" Whittaker faced multiple-time BJJ world champion Jacare Souza at UFC on FOX: Johnson vs Reis. After dropping Souza with an overhand right earlier in the second round, Whittaker landed a massive head kick to send Souza to the canvas again, finishing the fight with heavy ground and pound.
event: UFC Fight Night: Johnson vs Reis

name: BILLY GOFF | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 26, 2023
description: Coming back from major adversity early in the first round, Billy Goff walks down Yusaku Kinoshita, landing a straight right punch to the body which shuts Kinoshita down and follows up with ground and pound to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs The Korean Zombie

name: YAIR RODRIGUEZ | UFC 284
description: One of the most dynamic strikers the Octagon has ever seen, Yair "El Pantera" Rodriguez flipped the script in his interim featherweight title bout against knockout artist Josh Emmett. After a competitive first round, Rodriguez landed a flying knee and then wrapped Emmett up in full guard and while landing massive elbows from bottom, he attacked an armbar and transitioned to triangle, finishing his first submission win in UFC.
event: UFC 284

name: ALEXANDRE PANTOJA | UFC 290
description: Proving that he is one of the most well-rounded flyweights in the world for a second time against the flyweight champion Brandon Moreno, Alexandre "The Cannibal" Pantoja was able to hold his own wherever the fight took him at UFC 290, showing punishing striking and opportunistic jiu-jitsu over five rounds to capture the flyweight title.
event: UFC 290

name: KAI KARA-FRANCE | UFC 269
description: En route to an interim title opportunity against Brandon Moreno, Kai Kara-France dismantled former bantamweight champion Cody Garbrandt in round one, landing a massive over hand right and follow up combination to finish the fight via KO.
event: UFC 269

name: GEORGES ST-PIERRE | UFC 79
description: Capping off a trilogy that showed he would usher in a new era of the welterweight division, Georges "Rush" St-Pierre submitted Matt Hughes via armbar at UFC 79, earning an interim UFC title in the process.
event: UFC 79

name: MICHAEL CHIESA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 03, 2024
description: Season 15 winner of The Ultimate Fighter and a household name in the welterweight division, Michael "Maverick" Chiesa aimed to end his three-fight losing streak against former interim champion Tony Ferguson. With less than two minutes remaining in the first round, Chiesa secured a takedown, quickly took Ferguson's back, locked in a body triangle, and secured a rear-naked choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Nurmagomedov

name: DEMIAN MAIA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 27, 2016
description: En route to his title shot against Tyron Woodley, Demian Maia made short work of Carlos Condit, submitting him via rear-naked choke in round one of their main event matchup in front of an appreciative Canadian crowd.
event: UFC Fight Night: Maia vs Condit

name: AIEMANN ZAHABI | UFC 289
description: Younger brother of famed coach Firas Zahabi, Aiemann Zahabi lands a massive knockout blow to Aoriqileng following a caught leg kick, earning a stellar result in front of his home crowd in Vancouver.
event: UFC 289

name: MATT HUGHES | UFC 60
description: In a matchup of UFC legends, Matt Hughes finished the man that started it all, Royce Gracie, in dramatic fashion, taking the Brazilian's back and landing thunderous ground and pound until the referee's stoppage.
event: UFC 60

name: NICOLAS DALBY | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 4, 2023
description: Earning a finish against all odds, Nicholas "Danish Dynamite" Dalby stopped the undefeated streak of Gabriel Bonfim at UFC Fight Night: Almeida vs Lewis, weathering an early storm before landing a massive knee and follow-up with ground and pound strikes to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Almeida vs Lewis

name: REINIER DE RIDDER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 09, 2024
description: Reinier "RdR" de Ridder took on Gerald Meerschaert at UFC Fight Night: Magny vs Prates in his UFC debut. After a series of high-level scrambles, de Ridder secured an arm-triangle submission early in the third round, earning the 14th submission victory of his professional MMA career.
event: UFC Fight Night: Magny vs Prates

name: CHAS SKELLY | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 19, 2022
description: Chas "The Scrapper" Skelly lands a dazing elbow on Mark Striegl, following up with a huge knee from the clinch that ensures the victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Walker vs Hill

name: SHAVKAT RAKHMONOV | UFC 285
description: In extending his finish streak to 17, Shavkat "Nomad" Rakhmonov put a pace on Geoff Neal, landing a multitude of strikes over three rounds and eventually finding an unconventional standing rear-naked choke finish against the fence.
event: UFC 285

name: MARC-ANDRE BARRIAULT | UFC 285
description: Putting a pace on Julian Marquez for the entirety of their UFC 285 matchup, Marc-Andre "Powerbar" Barriault slowly picked his opponent apart over two rounds, ramping up his pressure until the referee was forced to step in.
event: UFC 285

name: JUN YONG PARK | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 15, 2023
description: Jun Yong "The Iron Turtle" Park showed why he remains one of the toughest tests in the middleweight division against a talented prospect in Albert Duraev at UFC Fight Night: Holm vs Bueno Silva. Park landed a massive left hook to drop Duraev before sinking in a rear-naked choke in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holm vs Bueno Silva

name: BELAL MUHAMMAD | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEP 17, 2016
description: Earning the first finish of his UFC career, Belal "Remember the Name" Muhammad wilted Augusto Montano with his pace before taking his back and landing ground and pound to finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Poirier vs Johnson

name: LUKE ROCKHOLD | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 18, 2015
description: While he may have some of the flashiest kicks that the middleweight division has ever seen, former champion Luke Rockhold showed his world-class grappling pedigree in this matchup against Lyoto Machida. After tiring Machida, Rockhold forced his way to Machida's back, flattening out the Brazilian and sinking in the rear-naked choke in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Machida vs Rockhold

name: NURSULTON RUZIBOEV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 1, 2023
description: Landing one of the slickest one-punch KOs the Octagon has ever seen, Nursulton "Black" Ruziboev caught the leg kick of Brunno Ferreira before knocking out the Brazilian with a massive overhand right in round 1.
event: UFC Fight Night: Strickland vs Magomedov

name: JOHN MAKDESSI | UFC 129
description: Delivering one of the craziest spinning KOs in UFC history, John "The Bull" Makdessi feints a body kick in the third round of his fight with Kyle Watson, and as Watson brings his hands down, Makdessi spins and lands a back fist with fight-ending intention.
event: UFC 129

name: KATLYN CERMINARA | UFC 255
description: Katlyn "Blonde Fighter" Cerminara lands a barrage of punches in a victory over Cynthia Calvillo.
event: UFC 255

name: DOMINICK CRUZ | UFC 178
description: Dominick "The Dominator" Cruz makes a triumphant return to the Octagon against Takeya Mizugaki at UFC 178 by overwhelming the Japanese bantamweight a minute into the first round.
event: UFC 178

name: MERAB DVALISHVILI | UFC 298
description: After a back-and-forth first round, Merab "The Machine" Dvalishvili outpaced former champion Henry Cejudo, beating him at every point. Late in the third round, Merab carried Cejudo across the Octagon, slammed him, and delivered heavy ground and pound to put a stamp on his dominant performance.
event: UFC 298

name: CAIO BORRALHO | UFC 301
description: Fighting out of the southpaw stance, Caio "The Natural" Borralho controlled the distance with his right hand, landing heavy, accurate jabs at will, avoiding any threat of Paul Craig's takedown attempts. Borralho's success with the jab set up his power punches in the second round, culminating in an epic knockout victory against the fence in the second round.
event: UFC 301

name: BRIAN ORTEGA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 24, 2024
description: Leveraging position with an underhook early in the third round of their five-round Co-Main event, Brian "T-City" Ortega swept former UFC interim featherweight champion Yair Rodriguez to the mat, immediately transitioning into full mount. Following a heavy elbow from the mount, Ortega locked in an arm triangle submission, coming out victorious in the rematch after a loss in their first meeting.
event: Noche UFC

name: DREW DOBER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 17, 2022
description: Pressuring Bobby "King" Green to the fence midway through the second round, Drew Dober delivered a powerful left hand to secure the knockout victory after withstanding a heavy shot in pursuit of the finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Cannonier vs Strickland

name: TRESEAN GORE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 29, 2022
description: As Josh Fremd was grappling Tresean Gore against the fence, Gore wrapped up a guillotine and used it to force Fremd to his back, tightening the choke along the way until the submission finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Kattar vs Allen

name: MANEL KAPE | UFC 265
description: After 2 losses to start his UFC career, Manel "StarBoy" Kape exploded into a flying knee, finishing Ode Osborne in style to etch his name in the UFC win column. Bouncing in and out of range, Kape utilized his footwork and constant stance switches to bait Osburne in and earn the knockout with only 15 seconds left in the first round.
event: UFC 265

name: RAQUEL PENNINGTON | UFC 181
description: Following a split decision loss to future champion Jessica Andrade at UFC 171, Raquel "Rocky" Pennington refused to let the fight go the distance in her submission victory over Ashlee Evans-Smith at UFC 181, becoming only the 4th person in UFC history to win via bulldog choke.
event: UFC 181

name: KEVIN HOLLAND | UFC 302
description: Dubbed "Big Mouth" by UFC President Dana White, Kevin Holland is known to trade words with his opponents inside the Octagon. At UFC 302, Kevin "Trailblazer" Holland showed he trades more than just words, finishing Michal Oleksiejczuk by armbar submission only 94 seconds into the first round.
event: UFC 302

name: DUSTIN POIRIER | UFC 257
description: One of the most entertaining athletes to ever grace the Octagon, Dustin "The Diamond" Poirier rendered a historic performance on UFC's Fight Island at UFC 257 against "The Notorious" Conor McGregor. After stunning the Irishman with a big left hand, Poirier unleashed a flurry of punches, landing a finishing right hook, becoming the first person to finish McGregor by knockout.
event: UFC 257

name: ISLAM MAKHACHEV | UFC 280
description: Islam Makhachev dominated on the feet against Charles "Do Bronx" Oliveira, utilizing his strength to control positioning in grappling exchanges, and steering clear of the submission threat Oliveira presents. With about two minutes left in the second round, Makhachev knocked down the former champ with a counter right hook and jumped onto an arm triangle as soon as Oliveira hit the canvas, capturing the lightweight title at UFC 280 in Abu Dhabi.
event: UFC 280

name: KARINE SILVA | UFC 292
description: Undefeated flyweight prospect Karine Silva added another submission finish to her resume at UFC 292, cinching up a guillotine to tap Maryna Moroz at the final second of round 1.
event: UFC 292

name: JESSICA ANDRADE | UFC 237
description: A physical force unlike anyone before at 115lbs, Jessica "Bate Estaca" Andrade dethroned Rose Namajunas in devastating fashion at UFC 237, using a single leg to pick Namajunas up and slam her on her head.
event: UFC 237

name: JUSTIN TAFA | UFC 293
description: Rematching a bout that ended in a no contest due to eye poke, Justin "Bad Man" Tafa left no doubt against Austen Lane at UFC 293, landing a big right hook to stun his opponent and follow up left hook to put him down.
event: UFC 293

name: KALINN WILLIAMS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 18, 2024
description: Known for his massive punching power, Williams is a force to be reckoned with in the welterweight division. Needing only 90 seconds to find his range, Williams connected with a blistering overhand right, knocking out opponent Carlston Harris.
event: UFC Fight Night: Barboza vs Murphy

name: DOMINICK REYES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUN 8, 2024
description: After losing 4 straight fights, former title challenger Dominick "The Devastator" Reyes needed to get back into the win column, putting his top 15 ranking on the line against unranked opponent Dustin Jacoby. Almost 2 minutes into the first round, Reyes wobbled Jacoby with a swift counter left hook, followed by a knee up the middle, and several punches along the fence to secure the TKO victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Cannonier vs Imavov

name: RAUL ROSAS | UFC 282
description: Capitalizing on his breakthrough performance at Dana White's Contender Series, Raul Rosas became the youngest UFC fighter to win a debut at UFC 282, earning a submission finish over Jay Perrin via neck crank in round 1.
event: UFC 282

name: BO NICKAL | UFC 300
description: Undefeated at the start of his UFC career, former three-time NCAA national wrestling champion and rising middleweight contender Bo Nickal earned a spot in the main card opener at UFC 300, facing Cody Brundage. After a dominant first round filled with takedowns and control time, Nickal continued his onslaught in the second round, taking Brundage to the ground, securing his back, and sinking in a rear-naked choke.
event: UFC 300

name: TOM ASPINALL | UFC 295
description: When undisputed champion Jon Jones pulled out from his scheduled main event matchup at UFC 295, Tom Aspinall stepped in on two weeks' notice to face a man who may be the most devastating finisher in the heavyweight division, Sergei Pavlovich. Aspinall made the most of the opportunity, flipping the script and knocking out Pavlovich in round 1, becoming the interim heavyweight champion in the process.
event: UFC 295

name: MAX HOLLOWAY | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 15, 2023
description: Max "Blessed" Holloway demonstrated his exceptional striking prowess against Arnold Allen, leading to a unanimous decision victory in their highly-anticipated bout in Kansas City
event: UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs Allen

name: GILLIAN ROBERTSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 15, 2023
description: Gillian "The Savage" Robertson handles undefeated Venezuelan prospect Piera Rodriguez in her strawweight debut with suffocating top pressure that eventually leads to a second-round armbar. This is the seventh submission of Roberston's career, strengthening her reputation as one of the best grapplers in UFC.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs Allen

name: JOSH EMMETT | UFC 296
description: Featherweight knockout artist Josh Emmett put his jaw-dropping power on display at UFC 296, sitting down on an overhand right in the first round that immediately floored Bryce Mitchell.
event: UFC 296

name: MOLLY MCCANN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUL 23, 2022
description: Following up her legendary spinning elbow KO of Luana Carolina, Molly McCann went back to the well at UFC Fight Night: Blaydes vs Aspinall, rocking Hannah Goldy badly before landing another spinning back elbow against the fence to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Blaydes vs Aspinall

name: STEPHEN ERCEG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 02, 2024
description: Opening up the main card at UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Gaziev, Steve "Astroboy" Erceg looked to continue his two-fight win streak to start off his UFC career, facing top flyweight contender Matt "Danger" Schnell. After an absolute slugfest of a first round, Erceg caught Schnell with a devastating left hook on the tail end of a combo, finishing the fight only 26 seconds into the second round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Gaziev

name: PAYTON TALBOTT | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 18, 2023
description: Undefeated bantamweight, Payton Talbott earned his first UFC finish against Nick Aguirre at UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig, forcing his way to mount in round 3 before taking the back and securing the rear-naked choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig

name: SEAN BRADY | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 02, 2023
description: Sean Brady wasted no time in welcoming former UFC middleweight title challenger Kelvin Gastelum back to the welterweight division, taking his back less than a minute into the first round. After racking up 4 takedowns and almost 8 minutes of control time over the first two rounds, Brady got in on a single-leg takedown early in the third round, smoothly transitioned into full mount, and snatched up an arm in the ensuing scramble, locking in the Kimura submission to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dariush vs Tsarukyan

name: STIPE MIOCIC | UFC 241
description: In a highly anticipated rematch, Stipe Miocic faced Daniel Cormier at UFC 241, determined to reclaim his UFC heavyweight title. After a hard-fought battle, Miocic unleashed a barrage of body shots in the fourth round, leading to a decisive TKO victory. His performance ignited his second UFC title reign and secured his place as the most decorated heavyweight champion in UFC history.
event: UFC 241

name: DRICUS DU PLESSIS | UFC 305
description: With no shortage of pre-fight tension, UFC Middleweight Champion Dricus "Stillknocks" Du Plessis took on former two-time middleweight champion Israel "The Last Stylebender" Adesanya for his first title defense. After three rounds of back-and-forth action, Du Plessis connected with a couple of heavy right hands, sending Adesayna to the canvas, before taking his back and finishing the fight by submission via rear naked choke.
event: UFC 305

name: CARLOS ULBERG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 11, 2024
description: Needing only 12 seconds in the first round, Ulberg made quick work of ranked opponent Alonzo "Atomic" Menifield. At the top of the round, Menifield blitzed Ulberg, throwing consecutive punches at full power. Ulberg slipped the oncoming punches, countering with a combination of his own, sending Menifield to the canvas in a flurry of punches.
event: UFC Fight Night: Lewis vs Nascimento

name: BILL ALGEO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 15, 2023
description: Bill "Senor Perfecto" Algeo flipped the script on TJ Brown at UFC Fight Night: Kansas City, dropping Brown with a jab before working his way to a rear naked choke finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs Allen

name: CHRIS CURTIS | UFC 282
description: Known for his exciting fighting style and pinpoint boxing, Chris "Action Man" Curtis put his skills on display in his bout against Joaquin Buckley at UFC 282. After a high-paced first round, Curtis turned the tide in the second by catching a body kick and countering with a perfectly-timed left hand, sending Buckley crashing to the canvas.
event: UFC 282

name: MARIA GODINEZ GONZALEZ | NOCHE UFC
description: Putting on a dominant grappling performance in front of her home crowd at Noche UFC, Maria Godinez Gonzalez sunk in a deep rear naked choke on Elise Reed in round two of their featured prelim matchup.
event: Noche UFC

name: MERAB DVALISHVILI | NOCHE UFC
description: Undefeated in his last 10 fights and coming off a victory over Olympic gold medalist and former double champion Henry "Triple C" Cejudo, Merab "The Machine" Dvalishvili earned a title shot against bantamweight superstar "Suga" Sean O'Malley at Noche UFC in Las Vegas at Sphere. From round one, Dvalishvili put on a show, taunting O'Malley with his own gestures and out-grappling him through five competitive rounds, ultimately besting the champion to capture UFC gold on the highest stage.
event: Noche UFC

name: HOLLY HOLM | UFC 193
description: Shattering the 12-fight unbeaten streak and superstar status of Ronda Rousey in the blink of an eye, "The Preacher's Daughter" Holly Holm produced one of the most surprising upsets in the sport's history at UFC 193, delivering the 'head-kick heard around the world' in round 2.
event: UFC 193

name: QUINTON JACKSON | PRIDE FC 2004
description: Quinton "Rampage" Jackson delivered one of the most iconic knockouts in MMA history at Pride Critical Countdown 2004 against Ricardo Arona. Trapped in a triangle choke after absorbing several punishing upkicks, Jackson showcased his raw power with a thunderous slam that instantly rendered Arona unconscious.
event: PRIDE FC 2004

name: AMANDA RIBAS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 18, 2023
description: Brazilian fan favorite, Amanda Ribas displayed a much-improved striking game at UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig against Luana Pinheiro, landing a massive spinning hook kick and follow-up combination to finish the fight in round 3.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig

name: TAGIR ULANBEKOV | UFC 296
description: Tagir Ulanbekov showcased his elite grappling at UFC 296, earning a hard-fought submission victory over Cody Durden. After a first-round knockdown and two expertly executed takedowns, Ulanbekov took Durden's back late in the second round and secured a rear-naked choke to seal the win.
event: UFC 296

name: DIEGO LOPES | UFC 300
description: After landing a couple of hard calf kicks to begin the round, Diego Lopes connected with a devastating right uppercut, left hook combination to send ranked featherweight contender "Super" Sodiq Yusuff to the canvas. Once the fight got back up to the feet, Lopes landed another heavy uppercut, knocking Yusuff to the ground, finishing the fight via TKO from the back mount.
event: UFC 300

name: CHAEL SONNEN | UFC 136
description: Renowned for his charismatic personality and trash talk outside the Octagon, Chael Sonnen showcased his MMA skills at UFC 136 with a commanding performance against Brian Stann, garnering nearly eight minutes of control time and landing over 100 total strikes before finishing the fight with a second-round arm triangle. Following the fight, Sonnen seized the opportunity in his post-fight interview to challenge light heavyweight champion Anderson Silva to a rematch.
event: UFC 136

name: ALISTAIR OVEREEM | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY, 8 2016
description: Alistair "The Demolition Man" Overeem connects with a beautiful jumping switch kick followed by heavy ground-and-pound to finish former champion Andrei Arlovski and earning a shot at the UFC heavyweight Title.
event: UFC Fight Night: Overeem vs Arlovski

name: CHAN SUNG JUNG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 15, 2012
description: One of the best to ever compete in the featherweight division, "The Korean Zombie" Chan Sung Jung earns a submission in his first UFC main event via D'Arce choke after dropping Dustin Poirier with an upper-cut, hook combination, and follow-up flying knee. This high-profile victory earned him a title shot against Jose Aldo.
event: UFC Fight Night: The Korean Zombie vs Poirier

name: ABUS MAGOMEDOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEP 03, 2022
description: Training out of Dusseldorf, Germany, Abus Magomedov matched up against Dustin Stoltzfus in his UFC debut at UFC Fight Night: Gane vs Tuivasa. Just twelve seconds into the first round, Magomedov landed a powerful teep kick to Stoltzfus's chin, quickly following up with a barrage of punches against the fence to finish the fight by TKO.
event: UFC Fight Night: Gane vs Tuivasa

name: ANDRE FILI | UFC 296
description: Andre "Touchy" Fili put on a clinic at UFC 296, showcasing his speed and precision against Lucas Almeida. Late in the first round, Fili capitalized on a perfectly timed counter, landing a thunderous right hand followed by a barrage of punches to secure the TKO victory.
event: UFC 296

name: YOEL ROMERO | UFC 205
description: Known for his explosive power, Yoel "Soldier of God" Romero delivered a highlight-reel knockout against Chris Weidman at UFC 205. Facing the former middleweight champion in front of his hometown crowd, Romero landed a flying knee in the third round, earning a spectacular victory and securing a shot at the UFC middleweight title.
event: UFC 205

name: VITOR BELFORT | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 18, 2013
description: In a clash between elite strikers, Vitor "The Phenom" Belfort delivered one of the most iconic finishes in UFC history against Luke Rockhold at UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs Rockhold. Unleashing a spinning heel kick that landed flush, Belfort knocked out the former Strikeforce champion in Rockhold's UFC debut, solidifying his reputation as one of the sport's most electrifying finishers.
event: UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs Rockhold

name: JOSHUA VAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 13, 2024
description: Joshua "The Fearless" Van put on a dominant performance against Felipe Bunes at UFC Fight Night: Ankalaev vs Walker 2. With relentless pressure and sharp striking, Van overwhelmed Bunes in a high-paced battle, securing a TKO victory late in the second round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Ankalaev vs Walker 2

name: RAMIZ BRAHIMAJ | UFC 309
description: Ramiz Brahimaj made a statement at UFC 309 with an awesome performance against Mickey Gall. Just under three minutes into the first round, Brahimaj connected with a big right hand to earn his first UFC knockout victory
event: UFC 309

name: CHUCK LIDDELL | UFC 47
description: Former training partners Chuck "The Iceman" Liddell and Tito "The Huntington Beach Bad Boy" Ortiz squared off at UFC 47, both coming off losses to Randy Couture. About thirty seconds into the second round, Liddell seized his opportunity and unleashed a vicious combination against the fence, dropping Ortiz with a powerful straight right for the knockout victory.
event: UFC 47

name: MINGYANG ZHANG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 23, 2024
description: The Mountain Tiger Mingyang Zhang thrilled his home crowd with an epic performance against Ozzy Diaz at UFC Fight Night: Yan vs Figueiredo. Halfway through the first round, Zhang connected with a short lead elbow to drop Diaz, and followed up with heavy ground strikes to earn his second first-round finish in as many UFC fights.
event: UFC Fight Night: Yan vs Figueiredo

name: DANIEL HOOKER | UFC 290
description: Daniel "The Hangman" Hooker faced Jalin "The Tarantula" Turner at UFC 290 in a thrilling Fight of the Night performance. Despite absorbing a head kick from Turner that would have dropped most fighters, Hooker showcased his resilience and heart, rallying to secure a hard-fought decision victory through sheer will and determination.
event: UFC 290

name: OBAN ELLIOTT | UFC 309
description: Oban "The Welsh Gangster" Elliott showcased his grit and tenacity against Bassil Hafez at UFC 309. After attacking Hafez's lead leg throughout the first two rounds, Elliott dropped him with a powerful overhand right in round three, finishing with heavy ground and pound.
event: UFC 309

name: YOUSSEF ZALAL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 02, 2024
description: Youssef "The Moroccan Devil" Zalal faced off against Jack Shore in a featherweight clash at UFC Fight Night: Moreno vs Albazi. After knocking Shore to the ground with a flawless standing knee, Zalal secured an arm-triangle choke with a minute left in the second round, earning his third consecutive victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Moreno vs Albazi

name: TOM ASPINALL | UFC 304
description: After a freak injury led to a loss in their first meeting, Tom Aspinall sought to settle the score in his first interim title defense against Curtis "Razor" Blaydes at UFC 304. Aspinall left no questions unanswered, connecting with a powerful lead left that knocked Blaydes down and finishing the fight with heavy ground-and-pound just a minute into the first round.
event: UFC 304

name: ALEX PEREZ | UFC 250
description: Over the last ten years, the low-calf kick has become a staple of high-level mixed martial arts, consistently proving its effectiveness time and time again. At UFC 250: Nunes vs Spencer, Alex Perez battered Jussier Formiga's calf immediately and eventually found a TKO stoppage later in the first due to leg kicks.
event: UFC 250

name: JASMINE JASUDAVICIUS | UFC 297
description: Jasmine Jasudavicius showcased her elite wrestling skillset against Priscila Cachoeira in front of her home crowd at UFC 297, racking up over 11 minutes of control time in the first two rounds. In the third, she unleashed heavy ground-and-pound from the crucifix position before locking in an anaconda submission to secure the victory.
event: UFC 297

name: GREGORY RODRIGUES | UFC 292
description: After suffering his first UFC career knockout loss, Gregory "Robocop" Rodrigues bounced back with an epic TKO performance against Denis Tiuliulin at UFC 292. Less than two minutes into the first round, Rodrigues landed a flawless takedown, transitioned to full mount, and unleashed a few heavy elbows that rendered Tiuliulin unconscious, prompting the referee to step in and stop the fight.
event: UFC 292

name: GABRIELLA FERNANDES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 23, 2024
description: Gabriella "Gabi" Fernandes shocked the crowd with an upset victory over Wang Cong at UFC Fight Night: Yan vs Figueiredo. After surviving an early onslaught, Fernandes dropped Cong with a huge left hand and quickly secured a rear-naked choke for the second round submission victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Yan vs Figueiredo

name: ILIA TOPURIA | UFC 298
description: Undefeated in his first six fights, Ilia "El Matador" Topuria faced featherweight champion and future Hall of Famer, Alexander "The Great" Volkanovski, in his quest for UFC gold. Three and a half minutes into the second round, Topuria closed the distance with a combination, landing a devastating right hook that knocked the champion out cold in stunning fashion.
event: UFC 298

name: SEAN WOODSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 14, 2024
description: Looking to extend his unbeaten streak, Sean Woodson took on Fernando Padilla at UFC Fight Night: Covington vs Buckley. With just seconds remaining in the opening round, Woodson unleashed a sharp uppercut-hook combination, followed by another right-left combo as Padilla backpedaled to earn the TKO victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Covington vs Buckley

name: VIRNA JANDIROBA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUL 20, 2024
description: On a three-fight win streak with eyes on a title shot, strawweight contender Virna "Carcara" Jandiroba secured her first main event fight against Amanda Lemos, facing her for the second time and seeking redemption after a loss in their first meeting. Determined not to lose again, Jandiroba showcased her exceptional grappling skills, taking Lemos's back, threatening with a rear-naked choke, and seamlessly transitioning to an armbar.
event: UFC Fight Night: Lemos vs Jandiroba

name: CHRIS BARNETT | UFC 268
description: Chris "Beast Boy" Barnett executes a flawless spinning wheel kick before finishing Gian Villante at UFC 268 and celebrating in equally epic fashion.
event: UFC 268

name: JEAN SILVA | UFC 303
description: Following a first-round KO in his debut, Dana White's Contender Series alum Jean "Lord" Silva stepped up in competition against Charles "Air" Jourdain at UFC 303. After scoring a knockdown in round one, Silva defended a takedown early in round two and landed a massive uppercut, knocking Jourdain out mid-scramble.
event: UFC 303

name: ALEXIA THAINARA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 22, 2025
description: Stepping in on short notice for her UFC debut, Alexia "Burguesinha" Thainara faced fan favorite Molly McCann at UFC Fight Night: Edwards vs Brady. Thainara made the most of the moment, locking in a rear-naked choke late in the first round to earn the submission win and silence the UK crowd.
event: UFC Fight Night: Edwards vs Brady

name: ALEXANDER VOLKOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 6, 2021
