description: Jake "The Prototype" Collier submits Chase Sherman via rear naked choke less than 3 minutes into the first round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Kattar vs Chikadze

name: KHABIB NURMAGOMEDOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 19, 2013
description: Khabib "The Eagle" Nurmagomedov finishes Thiago Tavares in the first round with a clean left uppercut and massive elbows on the ground for his third straight UFC victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs Bisping

name: JOSE ALDO | UFC 142
description: Jose Aldo lands a powerful knee to Chad Mendes to retain the UFC featherweight title in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
event: UFC 142

name: CHRIS WEIDMAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUL 11, 2012
description: Before his legendary title-winning performance, Chris Weidman made a statement at UFC Fight Night: Munoz vs Weidman. Facing top middleweight contender Mark Munoz, Weidman delivered a stunning standing elbow in the second round, followed by ground-and-pound to secure a TKO victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Munoz vs Weidman

name: JOE LAUZON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 25, 2015
description: Joe Lauzon takes Takanori Gomi to the canvas and secures the TKO via ground and pound.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dillashaw vs Barao 2

name: CONOR MCGREGOR | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 6, 2013
description: "The Notorious" Conor McGregor KOs Marcus Brimage with a barrage of powerful punches in his UFC debut.
event: UFC Fight Night: Mousasi vs Latifi

name: JAN BLACHOWICZ | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 16, 2017
description: Jan Blachowicz displays his elite striking ability landing a clean head-kick and multiple takedowns in a victory over Jared Cannonier.
event: UFC Fight Night: Lawler vs dos Anjos

name: JULIANNA PENA | UFC 269
description: Julianna "The Venezuelan Vixen" Pena claims the bantamweight title after submitting Amanda Nunes via rear naked choke in one of the biggest upsets in UFC History.
event: UFC 269

name: LYOTO MACHIDA | UFC 98
description: After a wild flurry of punches, Lyoto "The Dragon"  Machida lands a hard left hand knocking out Rashad Evans to claim the light heavyweight title.
event: UFC 98

name: SANTIAGO PONZINIBBIO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 17, 2018
description: Santiago "Argentine Dagger" Ponzinibbio delivers a powerful right-hand to secure the knockout victory against Neil Magny.
event: UFC Fight Night: Magny vs Ponzinibbio

name: KYLER PHILLIPS | UFC 271
description: Coming off his first UFC loss, Dana White's Contender Series alum Kyler "The Matrix" Phillips looked to bounce back against Marcelo Rojo at UFC 271. After securing full mount in the third round, Phillips capitalized on Rojo's fading defense and locked in a triangle armbar to earn the submission victory.
event: UFC 271

name: EMERALD KEY
description: Created as a commemoration of the UFC's 30th Anniversary, Emerald Keys are a special "Pack Insert" that unlocked a 1/1 Ultimate tier Moment in Series 2, with additional prizes along the way.

name: MANON FIOROT | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 20, 2021
description: In her UFC debut, Manon "The Beast" Fiorot finishes Victoria Leonardo with a flurry of punches after landing a powerful head kick.
event: UFC Fight Night: Chiesa vs Magny

name: BJ PENN | UFC 101
description: With UFC champion in two divisions already on the resume, BJ "The Prodigy" Penn defends his lightweight title against Kenny Florian locking in a rear-naked choke submission in the fourth round at UFC 101.
event: UFC 101

name: JOOSANG YOO | UFC 316
description: Entering the Octagon for the first time, Korean featherweight "Zombie Jr." Joo Sang Yoo made an instant statement against Jeka Saragih at UFC 316. Just 28 seconds in, Yoo landed a perfectly timed left hook that face-planted Saragih for a walk-off knockout, evoking shades of his namesake, The Korean Zombie.
event: UFC 316

name: ROBBIE LAWLER | UFC 195
description: "Ruthless" Robbie Lawler catches and drops Carlos Condit with a huge right hand in the second round of their epic welterweight title fight that saw Lawler retain his belt.
event: UFC 195

name: MARCUS MCGHEE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 29, 2023
description: Marcus McGhee makes a statement in his UFC debut, dropping Octagon veteran Journey Newson with a left hand halfway through the second round, transitioning to the back and sinking in a rear naked choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Song vs Simon

name: SAID NURMAGOMEDOV | UFC 270
description: Said Nurmagomedov sinks in a beautiful guillotine choke submission on Cody Stamann only 47 seconds into the first round.
event: UFC 270

name: DEMETRIOUS JOHNSON | UFC 216
description: Renowned for his precision and dominance in the flyweight division, Demetrious "Mighty Mouse" Johnson showcased his unparalleled grappling skills in a title defense against Ray Borg at UFC 216. Securing a spectacular flying armbar submission in the fifth round, Johnson earned his 7th finish in the division, breaking the record for the most finishes in UFC flyweight history. This victory solidified Johnson's legacy as one of the greatest flyweight mixed martial artists of all time.
event: UFC 216

name: AMANDA RIBAS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 29, 2019
description: Amanda Ribas takes Emily Whitmire's back and records a second-round submission victory in her UFC debut.
event: UFC Fight Night: Ngannou vs dos Santos

name: BRADY HIESTAND | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 22, 2023
description: Earning the first finish of his UFC career,  The Ultimate Fighter standout Brady Hiestand puts a pace on Batgerel Danaa for three rounds, using his grappling and ground and pound to wear on Danaa until the TKO finish in round 3.
event: UFC Fight Night: Pavlovich vs Blaydes

name: BJ PENN | UFC 46
description: Facing one of the most dominant champions in UFC history, BJ "The Prodigy" Penn moved up a weight class to challenge Matt Hughes for the welterweight title at UFC 46. In one of the biggest upsets in UFC history, Penn submitted the 6-time champion and then #1 pound-for-pound fighter in the world, capturing UFC gold and cementing his place among the sport's greats.
event: UFC 46

name: JON JONES | UFC 309
description: Making his first heavyweight title defense, Jon "Bones" Jones faced the legendary Stipe Miocic at UFC 309 in a blockbuster main event. From the outset, Jones showcased his signature striking, mixing in a variety of attacks and scoring an impressive trip takedown in the opening round. Late in the third round, Jones landed a perfectly timed spinning back kick to Miocic's body, sending him crashing to the canvas. The victory solidified Jones' reign as heavyweight champion and further cemented his legacy as the greatest mixed martial artist of all time.
event: UFC 309

name: BENOIT SAINT-DENIS | UFC 295
description: Former French special forces officer Benoit Saint-Denis added a head-kick knockout to his five-fight finish streak at UFC 295. As Matt Frevola disengaged from a grappling exchange against the fence, Saint-Denis followed his opponent, measured distance, and threw a left high kick flush to the temple.
event: UFC 295

name: MICHAEL BISPING | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 27, 2016
description: In a performance that earned him a shot at UFC gold, Michael "The Count" Bisping showed his otherworldly resilience after getting dropped with a flying knee while trying to recover his mouthpiece at the end of round 3. Bisping recomposed himself and came back to win the final two rounds and defeat one of the greatest of all time in Anderson Silva.
event: UFC Fight Night: Silva vs Bisping

name: ALEX PEREIRA | UFC 281
description: After tracking down his former kickboxing foe and rising through the middleweight ranks, Alex Pereira defeated Israel Adesanya in mixed martial arts, capturing a UFC title in the process. While the speed and technique of Adesanya kept Pereira at bay for the first four rounds, Pereira closed the distance in the fifth, landing massive hooks with Adesanya against the fence until the referee's stoppage.
event: UFC 281

name: MAX HOLLOWAY | UFC 231
description: Following up back-to-back title victories over fellow featherweight great Jose Aldo, Max Holloway put on a historic championship performance against Brian Ortega in Ontario, Canada, landing a record-breaking 290 significant strikes over four rounds. Holloway would later go on to shatter this record against Calvin Kattar.
event: UFC 231

name: HYUNSUNG PARK | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 09, 2023
description: HyunSung "Peace of Mind" Park made a statement at UFC Fight Night Song vs Gutierrez, delivering a dominant second round TKO against Shannon Ross. After methodically breaking down his opponent with a variety of powerful strikes, Park landed a perfectly placed body shot that sent Ross crumpling to the canvas.
event: UFC Fight Night: Song vs Gutierrez

name: CESAR ALMEIDA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 06, 2024
description: Cesar "Cesinha" Almeida showcased his takedown defense in his UFC debut against Dylan Budka in the featured prelim of UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Curtis 2. Dealing with relentless wrestling pressure, Almeida delivered brutal elbows with his back against the fence, securing a spectacular TKO victory in the second round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Curtis 2

name: BRANDON ROYVAL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 15, 2023
description: In a clash of top-5 flyweight contenders, Brandon "Raw Dawg" Royval faced Matheus Nicolau at UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs Allen in Kansas City, MO. Just two minutes into the first round, Royval landed a devastating knee that sent Nicolau to the canvas, finishing the fight with heavy elbows on the ground for a Performance of the Night bonus.
event: UFC Fight Night: Holloway vs Allen

name: MAX HOLLOWAY | UFC 300
description: Renowned for his willingness to face any challenger, former featherweight champion, Max "Blessed" Holloway, moved up to lightweight to compete against former interim champion, Justin Gaethje, for the UFC BMF title at UFC 300. With the scorecards in his favor, Holloway stepped to the center of the Octagon and pointed to the ground, challenging Gaethje to go all out in the final 10 seconds of the fifth round. In a moment that will inspire generations of fighters to come, Holloway delivered a walk-off KO in the last second of the fight, solidifying his status as the baddest man on the planet.
event: UFC 300

name: MAGOMED ANKALAEV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 13, 2024
description: After their first fight ended in a no contest due to a knee strike to a downed opponent, former title challenger, Magomed Ankalaev, sought to settle the score in a rematch against top-10 light heavyweight contender, Johnny Walker. A little over halfway through the second round, Ankalaev landed a crushing right hook that sent Walker to the canvas, sealing the fight with a final uppercut for the knockout victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Ankalaev vs Walker 2

name: MING SHI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 23, 2024
description: Ming Shi made her UFC debut at UFC Fight Night: Yan vs Figueiredo against Feng Xiaocan for the Road to UFC Season 3 strawweight tournament crown. Early in the third round, Shi landed a vicious right head kick to knock Xiaocan out, earning the victory in one of the year's best knockouts.
event: UFC Fight Night: Yan vs Figueiredo

name: DAVID ONAMA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUN 24, 2023
description: After a Fight of the Night performance in his last outing, David Onama looked to put on another show against Gabriel Santos at UFC Fight Night: Emmett vs Topuria. With a minute left in the second round, Onama landed several stinging close-range strikes, punctuated by a powerful uppercut that dropped Santos, then sealed the KO victory with a few follow-up shots before celebrating in homage to Israel Adesanya.
event: UFC Fight Night: Emmett vs Topuria

name: POLYANA VIANA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 05, 2022
description: Consistently improving her game each time she makes the walk to the Octagon, Polyana "Dama de Ferro" Viana landed a perfectly placed combination to counter Jinh Yu Frey's blitz at UFC Fight Night: Rodriguez vs Lemos, finishing the fight via TKO.
event: UFC Fight Night: Mitchell vs Evloev

name: AZAMAT MURZAKANOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 03, 2024
description: Undefeated in his first three UFC fights, Dana White's Contender Series alum Azamat "Professional" Murzakanov faced ranked light heavyweight  Alonzo "Atomic" Menifield at UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Nurmagomedov in Abu Dhabi. Dominating the striking exchanges up to that point, Murzakanov landed a powerful left hook late in the second round that hurt Menifield, following up with a combination to secure a second-round knockout.
event: UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Nurmagomedov

name: PAYTON TALBOTT | UFC 303
description: As the biggest betting favorite on the card, undefeated bantamweight prospect Payton Talbott took on Yanis "The Desert Warrior" Ghemmouri at UFC 303. Seconds into the first round, Talbott landed a pinpoint straight right hand that dropped Ghemmouri, and with the ref allowing it to continue, he finished the fight with a few follow-up shots on the ground.
event: UFC 303

name: ISRAEL ADESANYA | UFC 243
description: With unmatched striking and style, Israel "The Last Stylebender" Adesanya confirms his status as the undisputed middleweight champion of the world via a 2nd round TKO of Robert Whittaker at UFC 243.
event: UFC 243

name: MICHAEL MORALES | UFC 277
description: After a first-round KO in his debut, Dana White's Contender Series alum, Michael Morales, squared off against fellow welterweight prospect, Adam Fugitt, at UFC 277. Nearly a minute into the third round, Morales landed a crisp one-two combination that staggered Fugitt, then sealed the victory with relentless strikes along the fence.
event: UFC 277

name: SHARABUTDIN MAGOMEDOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUN 22, 2024
description: Known for his sensational Muay Thai skills, highly anticipated middleweight prospect, Sharabutdin "Bullet" Magomedov put his skills on display against Antonio "Malvado" Trocoli at UFC Fight Night: Whittaker vs Aliskerov. After landing a perfectly timed knee to counter Trocoli's takedown, Magomedov unleashed a barrage of punches, ultimately sending him to the canvas with a final left hook late in the third round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Whittaker vs Aliskerov

name: MUHAMMAD NAIMOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUN 03, 2023
description: Muhammad "Hillman" Naimov earned his first UFC win at UFC Fight Night: Kara-France vs Albazi, dropping Jamie Mullarkey with a massive counter left hook midway through round two.
event: UFC Fight Night: Kara-France vs Albazi

name: CHARLES OLIVEIRA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT AUG 1, 2010
description: In his UFC debut, Charles "Do Bronx" Oliveira submits Darren Elkins via triangle armbar in the first round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Jones vs Matyushenko

name: ANTHONY HERNANDEZ | UFC 298
description: Riding a four-fight win streak, Anthony "Fluffy" Hernandez faced knockout artist Roman Kopylov at UFC 298. After some early success on the feet and solid takedown defense from Kopylov, Hernandez secured a takedown in the second round and locked in a rear-naked choke to earn the submission victory and extend his streak to five.
event: UFC 298

name: AMIR ALBAZI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 17, 2022
description: Unbeaten through three fights to start off his UFC career, Amir "The Prince" Albazi took on Alessandro Costa at UFC Fight Night: Cannonier vs Strickland. A little over two minutes into the third round, Albazi connected with a sharp uppercut before following up with heavy ground strikes to earn his first knockout victory inside the Octagon.
event: UFC Fight Night: Cannonier vs Strickland

name: GABRIEL BONFIM | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 15, 2025
description: Following his only decision victory in the UFC, Gabriel "Marretinha" Bonfim aimed to return to his finishing ways against Kalinn "Khaos" Williams at UFC Fight Night: Cannonier vs Rodrigues. After controlling the action with sharp jabs and leg kicks, Bonfim secured a slick takedown late in the second round, then locked in a D'arce choke during a scramble to render Williams unconscious with just two seconds remaining.
event: UFC Fight Night: Cannonier vs Rodrigues

name: ANDERSON SILVA | UFC 126
description: Anderson "The Spider" Silva defends the UFC middleweight title with an epic front-kick KO of the legend Vitor Belfort. This Knockout of the Night bonus winner is regarded as one of the most iconic KOs in UFC history.
event: UFC 126

name: KHAMZAT CHIMAEV | UFC 273
description: In a potential fight of the year contender, Khamzat \'Borz\' Chimaev goes the distance for the first time in his career against Gilbert Burns and emerges victorious after their slugfest brought the Jacksonville crowd to their feet.
event: UFC 273

name: ERIN BLANCHFIELD | UFC 281
description: Erin "Cold Blooded" Blanchfield shines brightly under the lights of Madison Square Garden at UFC 281, dominating Molly McCann on the ground and locking in a kimura submission.
event: UFC 281

name: ISMAEL BONFIM | UFC 283
description: After earning a decision win on Dana White's Contender Series Season 6, Ismael "Marreta" Bonfim looked to put the lightweight division on notice in his UFC debut against Terrance "T. Wrecks" McKinney at UFC 283. Midway through the second round, Bonfim landed a straight right hand that sent McKinney's mouthguard flying, then followed up with a perfectly timed flying knee, dropping McKinney face down on the canvas.
event: UFC 283

name: CARLA ESPARZA | THE ULTIMATE FIGHTER SEASON 20 FINALE
description: Carla "Cookie Monster" Esparza becomes the first UFC women's straweight champion by submitting Rose Namajunas via rear-naked choke.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 20 Finale

name: CUB SWANSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 14, 2024
description: Looking to make his 25th appearance inside the UFC Octagon, Cub "Killer" Swanson faced off against fellow featherweight veteran Billy Quarantillo at UFC Fight Night: Covington vs Buckley. After two competitive rounds, Swanson landed a devastating right hand in the third, dropping Quarantillo and earning his eighth Fight of the Night bonus with the knockout victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: Covington vs Buckley

name: MICHAEL MORALES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 17, 2025
description: Rising Ecuadorian star Michael Morales faced his toughest test to date in his first main event fight, taking on former title challenger Gilbert Burns at UFC Fight Night: Burns vs Morales. Morales passed with flying colors, stuffing takedowns and punishing Burns with sharp, accurate striking to earn a first-round TKO.
event: UFC Fight Night: Burns vs Morales

name: MATT SCHNELL | UFC 216
description: Matt "Danger" Schnell displays crisp striking to secure a unanimous decision victory over Marco Beltran
event: UFC 216

name: MICHELLE WATERSON | UFC 229
description: "The Karate Hottie" Michelle Waterson showcases her elite speed against Felice Herrig landing an assortment of clean strikes in a unanimous decision victory.
event: UFC 229

name: MICHEL PEREIRA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 18, 2019
description: With a breakdance introduction in his UFC debut, Michel "Demolidor" Pereira connects with a flying knee knockout victory over Danny Roberts.
event: UFC Fight Night: dos Anjos vs Lee

name: CHASE HOOPER | UFC 256
description: Chase "The Dream" Hooper finds a way to bring the fight to the ground where he puts Peter Barrett in a compromised position and locks in a rarely-seen heel hook submission at UFC 256.
event: UFC 256

name: MARLON VERA | UFC 268
description: Marlon "Chito" Vera lands a front kick against Frankie Edgar at UFC 268 in Madison Square Garden to notch his most notable victory so far, defeating a former UFC lightweight champion.
event: UFC 268

name: THE REAL MONEY FIGHT
description: Nate Diaz made this infamous post-fight callout of Conor McGregor late in 2015 before stepping in on short notice to do exactly that less than three months later at UFC 196.

name: SONG YADONG | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 29, 2023
description: Song "Kung Fu Kid" Yadong rebounds from the toughest loss of his career with a signature TKO victory over Ricky Simon who remains the last fighter to defeat top-ranked contender, Merab Dvalishvili. Not only did this win secure his position as one of the best bantamweights in the world, it put him back on track for a run at the title.
event: UFC Fight Night: Song vs Simon

name: CAIO BORRALHO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 29, 2023
description: Brazilian middleweight prospect, "The Natural" Caio Borralho extends his unbeaten streak in UFC against Michal Oleksiejczuk, shooting a perfectly-timed double leg and controlling the fight before securing the rear naked choke finish in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Song vs Simon

name: MY BALLS WAS HOT
description: To the confusion of everyone watching, Derrick Lewis took off his fight shorts after knocking out Alexander Volkov at UFC 229 in 2018. In the post-fight interview he was asked the question on everyone's mind, to which Lewis responded with this viral one-liner.

name: DRICUS DU PLESSIS | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 10, 2020
description: Dricus "Stillknocks" du Plessis lands a left hook for the first-round knockout in his UFC debut, as the South African fighter introduces himself to the middleweight division.
event: UFC Fight Night: Moraes vs Sandhagen

name: PETR YAN | UFC 245
description: Petr "No Mercy" Yan demonstrates his tremendous strength and power at UFC 245 while facing Urijah Faber, landing a knockout head kick at the start of the third round.
event: UFC 245

name: MICHELLE WATERSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 17, 2016
description: The "Karate Hottie" Michelle Waterson clinches fan favorite Paige VanZant against the fence, stepping through for a beautiful head and arm throw and immediately taking the back. VanZant tries to fight the hands for as long as she can, but Waterson is able to secure the rear naked choke finish in round 1.
event: UFC Fight Night: VanZant vs Waterson

name: BENEIL DARIUSH | UFC 248
description: Beneil Dariush goes from seeming on the verge of defeat himself to landing big shots on Drakkar Klose, turning the tide of their UFC 248 bout and scoring a walk-off knockout.
event: UFC 248

name: DAN HOOKER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 20, 2019
description: A feint with the right hand is followed by a sweeping left hook from Dan "The Hangman" Hooker that lands flush and knocks James Vick down. A few follow-up shots from Hooker ends the fight and earns him the KO victory.
event: UFC Fight Night: dos Anjos vs Edwards

name: SHOGUN RUA | UFC 134
description: Nearly four years after being submitted by Forrest Griffin, Mauricio "Shogun" Rua finally gets his revenge at UFC 134 via first-round knockout to even up the score.
event: UFC 134

name: SERGHEI SPIVAC | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 4, 2023
description: Serghei "Polar Bear" Spivac cements himself as a top 10 heavyweight contender by defeating the heavy-hitting Derrick Lewis via 1st-round submission. This secured the 2nd arm-triangle choke of his UFC career.
event: UFC Fight Night: Lewis vs Spivac

name: NICK DIAZ | UFC 62
description: Nick Diaz shows off his Gracie Jiu-Jitsu skills against Josh Neer at UFC 62, sinking in a kimura to get the tap and submission victory in the third round.
event: UFC 62

name: MUHAMMAD MOKAEV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 19, 2022
description: Muhammad "The Punisher" Mokaev wins his UFC debut in style with a flying knee that wobbles Cody Durden, allowing Mokaev to grab a guillotine choke and the submission victory in less than a minute.
event: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Aspinall

name: KURT HOLOBAUGH | UFC 292
description: Showcasing his oportunistic Jiu-Jitsu, Kurt Holobaugh attacks and armbar as Austin Hubbard rolls to escape, Holobaugh catches a triangle, finishing the fight via submission and winning a UFC contract.
event: UFC 292

name: ANTHONY JOHNSON | UFC 202
description: Anthony "Rumble" Johnson proves one shot is all it takes from the light heavyweight fighter to end an opponent's night, as an uppercut early in the first round knocks out Glover Teixeira at UFC 202.
event: UFC 202

name: BRANDON ROYVAL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 30, 2020
description: In his UFC debut, flyweight contender Brandon "Raw Dog" Royval survived some frantic grappling exchanges with UFC veteran Tim Elliot and eventually found the submission in round two. As Elliot tries to bridge out of mount, Royval floats on top position and snatches a head and arm choke on the way down, cutting through half guard with his knee and finishing the submission.
event: UFC Fight Night: Woodley vs Burns

name: STEPHEN ERCEG | UFC 289
description: In his UFC debut, Australian-born Steve "Astro Boy" Erceg stepped up on short notice to face top 15-ranked contender David Dvorak and passed that test with flying colors. Utilizing his footwork and speed, Erceg interrupts Dvorak's combinations with leg kicks and jabs, economically using his strikes to wear down Dvorak.
event: UFC 289

name: JON JONES | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 21, 2010
description: In his first-ever UFC main event, Jon "Bones" Jones dismantles Brandon Vera in the first round by landing some heavy elbows and punches from top position to secure the TKO win.
event: UFC Fight Night: Vera vs Jones

name: SEAN O'MALLEY | UFC 292
description: UFC superstar "Sugar" Sean O'Malley dethroned one of the best bantamweights ever to do it, Aljamain "Funk Master" Sterling, at UFC 292, landing a perfectly placed step back right hand in round 2 to floor the former champion, following up with punches on the ground to finish the fight.
event: UFC 292

name: JAMAHAL HILL | UFC 283
description: Just one month after a draw in the UFC 282 light heavyweight title match, Jamahal Hill and Glover Teixeira's main event at UFC 283 was elevated to a championship opportunity and Jamahal Hill capitalized in a big way. After stuffing a majority of Teixeira's takedown attempts in the first two rounds, Hill found his range and began picking Teixeira apart, utilizing his straight right hand and left high kick to rock Teixeira several times en route to a unanimous decision victory.
event: UFC 283

name: JIRI PROCHAZKA | UFC 300
description: After losing the light heavyweight title and tasting his first defeat in the Octagon in his last appearance, Jiri Prochazka aimed to get back on track for UFC gold in his matchup against Aleksander Rakic at UFC 300. After enduring several heavy leg kicks in the first round, Prochazka landed a vicious right hand midway through the second, following it up with an onslaught of strikes and relentless pressure to earn the TKO victory.
event: UFC 300

name: JIM MILLER | UFC 200
description: UFC veteran Jim "A-10" Miller faced Japanese legend Takanori Gomi at UFC 200 in a lightweight clash. Less than a minute into the fight, Miller caught Gomi's kick, taking the fight to the canvas and immediately threatening with submissions. As Gomi scrambled to regain his footing, Miller unleashed a barrage of vicious ground and pound, forcing the referee to stop the fight midway through the first round.
event: UFC 200

name: ALEXA GRASSO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 26, 2022
description: Alexa Grasso needs less than one round to finish Joanne Wood, landing a takedown and sinking in the rear-naked choke to win via submission.
event: UFC Fight Night: Blaydes vs Daukaus

name: ARNOLD ALLEN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 27, 2018
description: Weathering an early storm, Arnold "Almighty" Allen keeps his composure while being controlled against the fence, digging underhooks to attack the neck of Mads Burnell, finishing a modified guillotine choke.
event: UFC Fight Night: Thompson vs Till

name: ROBERT WHITTAKER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 26, 2016
description: Robert "The Reaper" Whittaker defends several of Derek Brunson's takedown attempts and catches him with a headkick into a left hook, eventually finding a TKO finish against the fence. This main event win among his countrymen in Melbourne, Australia primed the young contender for a title eliminator match against Ronaldo "Jacare" Souza.
event: UFC Fight Night: Whittaker vs Brunson

name: JORGE MASVIDAL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JAN 28, 2017
description: After dropping Donald "Cowboy" Cerrone at the end of the first round, Jorge "Gamebred" Masvidal picks up right where he left off, sending his opponent to the fence with a big overhand right. He follows up with punishing hooks to the body as Cerrone shells up, earning a TKO stoppage in R2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Volkov vs Aspinall

name: TATSURO TAIRA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 4, 2023
description: Undefeated flyweight prospect Tatsuro Taira showed world-class finishing instincts in his bout with Jesus Aguilar. Grappling early in the fight, Taira transitions to s-mount on Aguilar, rolling through to lock in the triangle from his back and as Aguilar postures up to defend, Taira extends the arm and forces Aguilar's head to the floor, finishing the fight via belly-down armbar.
event: UFC Fight Night: Lewis vs Spivac

name: ALESSANDRO COSTA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 17, 2023
description: Nullifying every attack from the tricky guard of Jimmy Flick, Alessandro "Nono" Costa keep his hips heavy and lands big elbows to the head, finishing the fight in round two.
event: UFC Fight Night: Vettori vs Cannonier

name: MOICANO WANTS MONEY
description: After submitting Brad Riddell at UFC 281, Renato Carneiro unleashed one of the strangest, yet electrifying post-fight interviews the Octagon has ever seen. In one breath urging the crowd to put some respect on his name, and in the other leaving them in stitches with classic one-liners, Renato finishes his rant with the now infamous phrase "Moicano Wants Money!" to an erupting crowd.

name: MATT SCHNELL | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 16, 2022
description: In one of the craziest rounds you will ever see, Matt "Danger" Schnell gets rocked by Mudaerji Su several times in round two at UFC Fight Night Ortega vs Rodriguez. Keeping his composure, Schnell works his way into a takedown and locks in a triangle as Mudaerji Su reverses to top position, finishing a comeback performance for the ages.
event: UFC Fight Night: Ortega vs Rodriguez

name: STEPHEN THOMPSON | UFC FIGHT NIGHT FEB 7, 2016
description: On his way up the rankings, Stephen "Wonderboy" Thompson defeated a prime Johnny Hendricks with one of the most stunning TKO finishes you will ever see. Countering the combinations of Hendricks early in the first, "Wonderboy" delivers a massive spinning back kick to the body, knocking Hendricks against the fence before finishing the fight with a flurry of punches.
event: UFC Fight Night: Hendricks vs Thompson

name: DONALD CERRONE | UFC 202
description: Delivering a combination that will live in UFC highlight reels for years, Donald "Cowboy" Cerrone turned back a surging contender in Rick Story at UFC 202. Cerrone counters Story's jab with one of his own, changes levels, lands a straight right to the body, throws a shovel uppercut to the chin, and finishes with a perfectly placed head kick to finish the fight.
event: UFC 202

name: ISAAC DULGARIAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 12, 2023
description: Dominating every moment of his UFC debut from top position, Isaac Dulgarian transitions to mount in the final minute of the first round and lands massive elbows until the TKO stoppage.
event: UFC Fight Night: Luque vs Dos Anjos

name: DERRICK LEWIS | UFC 229
description: Down on the scorecards and with time winding down, Derrick "The Black Beast" Lewis knew he needed a finish for a chance at a victory. After withstanding several shots to the lower body late in the third round, Lewis turned the tables on opponent Alexander Volkov, landing a huge overhand right sending Volkov to the canvas, followed up by relentless ground and pound to secure the comeback victory with just 11 seconds left in the fight.
event: UFC 229

name: JOHNNY WALKER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 17, 2018
description: Early in his UFC career, Johnny Walker showed extraordinary potential with every performance, as was evident in this fight with the always-tough Khalil Rountree Jr. Finding a muay thai clinch early in the first round, Walker controls Rountree's posture and lands two devastating short elbows to finish the fight.
event: UFC Fight Night: Magny vs Ponzinibbio

name: KAMARU USMAN | THE ULTIMATE FIGHTER SEASON 28 FINALE
description: Along a journey that eventually led to welterweight gold, Kamaru "Nigerian Nightmare" Usman thoroughly defeated one of the best in the world, Rafael Dos Anjos, dominating in top position for five rounds.
event: The Ultimate Fighter Season 28 Finale

name: MARCIN TYBURA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUNE 05, 2021
description: After eating several massive shots from heavyweight power-puncher Walt Harris, Marcin Tybura recomposes himself, initiating several grappling exchanges to slow down the pace of the fight, and after using a foot sweep to get top position, Tybura opens up with ground and pound, finishing the fight via TKO.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Sakai

name: ELVES BRENER | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 1, 2023
description: Surviving a grueling early onslaught from an outstanding lightweight prospect, Guram Kutateladze, Brazilian teammate of Charles Oliveira, Elves Brenner comes back and pours it on in the third round, landing a short left hook to put Kutateladze away.
event: UFC Fight Night: Strickland vs Magomedov

name: VOLKAN OEZDEMIR | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JUN 22, 2024
description: Opening up the main card at the first-ever UFC event in Saudi Arabia, Volkan "No Time" Oezdimir put his striking power on display, landing heavy calf kicks and punches in combination. About 2 minutes into the first round, Oezdimir connected with a leaping left hook to hurt Walker, finishing the fight with a vicious uppercut shortly thereafter.
event: UFC Fight Night: Whittaker vs Chimaev

name: KAYLA HARRISON | UFC 300
description: As a two-time Olympic gold medalist in judo and former judo world champion, Kayla Harrison drew top 5 contender and former women's bantamweight champion Holly Holm for her UFC debut fight at UFC 300. After dominating the first round with ground control and strikes from top position, Harrison secured back mount, sinking in a rear naked choke to defeat Holm early in the second round.
event: UFC 300

name: ANTHONY SMITH | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 27, 2018
description: Ahead of his title shot at UFC 235, Anthony "Lionheart" Smith showed the well-roundedness that has kept him at the top of the light heavyweight division for over a decade, out-grappling Volkan Oezdemir and finding a rear-naked choke finish in round 3.
event: UFC Fight Night: Oezdemir vs Smith

name: MATT BROWN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 13, 2023
description: One of the most prolific knockout artists in the history of UFC, Matt "The Immortal" Brown earned the 13th KO of his career against Court McGee at UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Almeida, further adding to his record of the most knockouts in the welterweight division.
event: UFC Fight Night: Rozenstruik vs Almeida

name: CHARLES JOURDAIN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 21, 2019
description: Forever the showman, Charles "Air" Jourdain lands a massive left hand as Dooho Choi charges in, knocking out the South Korean fighter in front of his home crowd at UFC Fight Night: Edgar vs Korean Zombie.
event: UFC Fight Night: Edgar vs Korean Zombie

name: BILLY QUARANTILLO | UFC FIGHT NIGHT SEP 12, 2020
description: Kicking off the main card at UFC Fight Night: Waterson vs Hill, Billy Quarantillo took on featherweight opponent Kyle Nelson, looking to add to his 4-fight win streak at the beginning of his UFC career. After a competitive first two rounds, the New York native Quarantillo landed a powerful overhand right, knocking Nelson out only seconds into the third round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Waterson vs Hill

name: KETLEN SOUZA | NOCHE UFC
description: Making her third appearance in the Octagon, strawweight contender Ketlen "Esquentadinha" Souza faced Yazmin Jauregui at Noche UFC at Sphere in Las Vegas. Entering the fight as nearly a 4/1 underdog, Souza silenced her doubters with a stunning performance, knocking Jauregui down with a massive left hook, quickly transitioning to a rear-naked choke to finish the fight in the first round.
event: Noche UFC

name: ARMAN TSARUKYAN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT DEC 2, 2023
description: Known for his complete, high-level skill set, Arman "Ahalkalakets" Tsarukyan is truly a force to be reckoned with in the lightweight division. After throwing a knee up the middle, Tsarukyan masterfully controlled his balance and connected with a huge overhand right before his foot even touched the ground, knocking out Beneil Dariush just one minute into the first round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dariush vs Tsarukyan

name: MARVIN VETTORI | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 23, 2021
description: After an unprecedented fight week weight-change that saw the bout moved from 185 to  205 Marvin Vettori put on a masterful striking performance, tiring Costa out over the course of 5 rounds.
event: UFC Fight Night: Costa vs Vettori

name: NASSOURDINE IMAVOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT JULY 24, 2021
description: One of the most talented striking prospects out of France, Nassourdine Imavov earned his first UFC finish against Ian Heinisch at UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Dillashaw, surgically finding massive shots against the fence before the TKO stoppage in round 2.
event: UFC Fight Night: Sandhagen vs Dillashaw

name: DIEGO FERREIRA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAY 20, 2023
description: Landing a knockout blow that stands out among his impressive resume of UFC finishes, Diego Ferreira unloaded a massive overhand right to the jaw of fellow veteran Michael Johnson, ending the fight in round two.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dern vs. Hill

name: DENISE GOMES | UFC 290
description: In a stunning performance at UFC 290, Denise "Dee" Gomes silenced the crowd with her ferocious striking against Yazmin Jauregui. Wasting no time, Gomes overwhelmed Jauregui with relentless pressure, delivering a flurry of punches that forced the referee to step in and stop the fight.
event: UFC 290

name: BRENDAN ALLEN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 18, 2023
description: Riding a five-fight win streak, Brendan "All In" Allen delivered a Performance of the Night at UFC Fight Night: Allen vs. Craig. After securing two takedowns and controlling the action for over seven minutes in the first two rounds, Allen maintained his dominance in the third, finishing Paul Craig with a rear-naked choke less than a minute into the round.
event: UFC Fight Night: Allen vs Craig

name: ROBBIE LAWLER | UFC 290
description: UFC Hall of Famer and former welterweight champion, "Ruthless" Robbie Lawler, prepared to make his final appearance in the Octagon at UFC 290 against fellow welterweight contender, Niko "The Hybrid" Price. Just half a minute into the first round, Lawler secured a clinch and landed a massive uppercut, delivering an epic KO to end his career in storied fashion.
event: UFC 290

name: KHABIB NURMAGOMEDOV | UFC 205
description: Khabib "The Eagle" Nurmagomedov put his dominant grappling on full display against Michael Johnson at UFC 205. After imposing relentless pressure, Nurmagomedov secured a takedown in the first round and methodically wore Johnson down before locking in a tight kimura in the third, forcing the tap and extending his undefeated record.
event: UFC 205

name: KING GREEN | UFC FIGHT NIGHT OCT 07, 2023
description: Headlining his second UFC event, King Green squared off against rising contender Grant Dawson at UFC Fight Night: Dawson vs Green. Just 30 seconds into the opening round, Green landed a thunderous left hand that dropped Dawson instantly, earning a stunning TKO victory in his second main event appearance.
event: UFC Fight Night: Dawson vs Green

name: NATE LANDWEHR | UFC FIGHT NIGHT MAR 30, 2024
description: Known for his relentless pace and fan-friendly style, Nate "The Train" Landwehr delivered an unforgettable finish against Jamall "Pretty Boy" Emmers at UFC Fight Night: Blanchfield vs Fiorot. Late in the first round, Landwehr uncorked a clean right hand, earning a KO victory in a fight that highlighted his durability and knockout power.
event: UFC Fight Night: Blanchfield vs Fiorot

name: BOGDAN GUSKOV | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 27, 2024
description: Fresh off his first UFC victory, Bogdan "Czarevitch" Guskov catapulted into the rankings after facing light heavyweight veteran Ryan "Superman" Spann at UFC Fight Night: Nicolau vs Perez. Despite giving up nearly three and a half minutes of control time in the first round, Guskov disoriented Spann with a vicious uppercut, following up with heavy ground strikes to secure the second-round finish.
event: UFC Fight Night: Nicolau vs Perez

name: CHANG HO LEE | UFC FIGHT NIGHT APR 05, 2025
description: Fresh off his Road to UFC tournament win, Chang Ho Lee looked to continue his winning ways against Cortavious Romious at UFC Fight Night: Emmett vs Murphy. After a dominant opening round, Lee secured top position in the second and unleashed a series of sharp elbows to earn the TKO and improve to 2-0 in UFC.
event: UFC Fight Night: Emmett vs Murphy

name: TALLISON TEIXEIRA | UFC 312
description: Brazil's Tallison "Xicao" Teixeira stepped into the spotlight on the main card of UFC 312 against heavy-hitting veteran Justin Tafa. Fighting in enemy territory, Teixeira silenced the Aussie crowd with a devastating right elbow for a walk-off knockout just 35 seconds into round one.
event: UFC 312

name: NATALIA CRISTINA DA SILVA | UFC FIGHT NIGHT NOV 19, 2022
description: Undefeated in UFC, Natalia Christina Da Silva landed a brutal spinning back kick KO on Tereza Bleda at UFC Fight Night: Nzechukwu vs Cutelaba. As Bleda changed levels to shoot for a takedown, Silva spun and threw a back kick to Bleda's face, ending the fight in round three.
event: UFC Fight Night: Lewis vs Spivac
